WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.542 --> 00:00:01.835
Praised be Jesus and Mary!

00:00:02.794 --> 00:00:04.754
Brothers and sisters in Christ.

00:00:08.091 --> 00:00:09.759
I am a little bit jealous of you.

00:00:11.386 --> 00:00:12.262
Do you know why?

00:00:15.306 --> 00:00:16.433
Even though you are young,

00:00:17.475 --> 00:00:19.728
you've come to the faith, relatively fast.

00:00:21.021 --> 00:00:22.939
I had to suffer a bit.

00:00:23.857 --> 00:00:25.942
However, everyone has their own path.

00:00:27.485 --> 00:00:30.113
I'll tell you my life story,

00:00:30.113 --> 00:00:31.906
which consists of two parts.

00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:34.451
The first part was

00:00:34.451 --> 00:00:35.744
without God.

00:00:35.744 --> 00:00:36.828
The second part is

00:00:36.828 --> 00:00:37.579
with God.

00:00:38.663 --> 00:00:39.914
Which part is better,

00:00:41.124 --> 00:00:42.542
you'll see for yourself.

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:47.005
As you know, my name 
is Goran. I was born in Split

00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:48.339
in a Catholic family,

00:00:49.257 --> 00:00:51.551
but there was no prayer

00:00:51.551 --> 00:00:52.677
or faith in my family,

00:00:52.677 --> 00:00:54.679
neither did we go to church.

00:00:54.679 --> 00:00:57.307
My parents would tell me
that I must go to church.

00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:58.683
I did not want to go,

00:00:58.683 --> 00:01:00.935
because I followed their example.

00:01:00.935 --> 00:01:03.813
I would tell them, if you don't 
attend church, why should I?

00:01:03.813 --> 00:01:07.025
My father was a difficult man and 
he made me attend religion classes.

00:01:08.985 --> 00:01:10.820
To me, church was boring.

00:01:11.446 --> 00:01:13.990
When you read the Ten Commandments,

00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:15.658
what is interesting about them?

00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:20.080
You are told not to steal, not to lie,
not to date someone else's wife.

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:21.748
Man, they forbid you to do anything.

00:01:21.748 --> 00:01:23.792
What kind of a life is that?

00:01:23.792 --> 00:01:27.087
That's the life for an old 
grandmother, who is waiting to die,

00:01:27.087 --> 00:01:29.255
and all she has left is prayer.

00:01:29.255 --> 00:01:32.092
I was sure that I received nothing from church.

00:01:33.343 --> 00:01:37.138
When my sister was four years old
she fell from the fifth floor. 

00:01:37.138 --> 00:01:39.057
She died at my mother's feet.

00:01:39.057 --> 00:01:41.267
When my brother was one year old,
he got meningitis and as a result,

00:01:41.267 --> 00:01:42.894
he remained deaf and mute.

00:01:42.894 --> 00:01:44.979
My mother was constantly
crying and depressive.

00:01:44.979 --> 00:01:46.356
At home there was no God,

00:01:46.356 --> 00:01:48.191
so my mother started to drink alcohol.

00:01:48.191 --> 00:01:50.652
The poor lady, she thought that
with alcohol, she'd get rid of

00:01:50.652 --> 00:01:52.028
the pain she carried in her heart.

00:01:52.654 --> 00:01:55.615
My father, who was a seaman,
spent more time at sea than at home.

00:01:56.783 --> 00:01:59.744
From a young age, I was either on 
the street or in front of the television. 

00:01:59.744 --> 00:02:02.247
I liked to watch American action movies.

00:02:02.247 --> 00:02:03.832
Those actors were my idols.

00:02:03.832 --> 00:02:08.670
They were full of tattoos, they had big 
muscles, they were in and out of prisons,

00:02:08.670 --> 00:02:11.131
they had beautiful women, 
great cars, and a lot of money.

00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:14.634
They smoked, and drank 
whiskey, man they were cool!

00:02:15.468 --> 00:02:19.055
I created a picture in my mind that
a man had to be like those actors.

00:02:19.556 --> 00:02:22.892
When I was ten years old, I started 
smoking cigarettes and drinking alcohol.

00:02:23.643 --> 00:02:26.855
When I was eleven years old, I was
sure I knew everything about life.

00:02:26.855 --> 00:02:29.941
I had enough of school, because all 
they ever did, was tell me what to do

00:02:29.941 --> 00:02:32.735
and how to behave. 
I had had enough of that,

00:02:32.735 --> 00:02:35.697
I thought I was old enough to live alone,

00:02:36.614 --> 00:02:38.158
so I ran away from home
and went to another city.

00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:41.119
I robbed a store. The police 
caught me and locked me up

00:02:43.288 --> 00:02:45.331
and obviously, they immediately 
called my father and told him 

00:02:45.331 --> 00:02:47.167
to come and pick 
me up the following day.

00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:49.252
My father left me with 
the police for three days.

00:02:49.711 --> 00:02:52.672
His reasoning was logical: leave him
there a few days longer, so that he

00:02:52.672 --> 00:02:54.382
gets scared and changes.

00:02:55.633 --> 00:02:57.635
The relationship between my father and I,

00:02:58.511 --> 00:03:02.015
to be honest, couldn't be called a relationship.

00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:03.516
My father was a good man,

00:03:03.516 --> 00:03:05.768
however he had a problem. 
He didn't know how to communicate.

00:03:05.768 --> 00:03:07.979
In our home, there were no conversations.

00:03:07.979 --> 00:03:11.191
My whole upbringing 
consisted of him beating me.

00:03:11.482 --> 00:03:14.694
I am ashamed to even mention
how much he beat me.

00:03:14.694 --> 00:03:17.655
He beat me like an ox, because he
thought that beatings would solve

00:03:17.655 --> 00:03:18.573
my problems.

00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:21.618
When he came to get me at the
police station after three days,

00:03:21.618 --> 00:03:22.952
he didn't ask me anything.

00:03:22.952 --> 00:03:25.788
He immediately began to 
beat me in the police station,

00:03:25.788 --> 00:03:29.334
to the point where the police
had to protect me from him.

00:03:30.752 --> 00:03:33.338
Afterwards, he beat me in the bus
for another two and a half hours.

00:03:34.005 --> 00:03:36.507
When I was thirteen years old,
my mother passed away.

00:03:36.966 --> 00:03:39.594
After her death I fell into a depression,

00:03:41.471 --> 00:03:46.684
because I had never hugged my mother,
kissed her or told her that I loved her. 

00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:51.606
I wanted to make those 
loving gestures towards her,

00:03:51.606 --> 00:03:53.775
but I couldn't because I was a man.

00:03:53.775 --> 00:03:55.818
Men don't show their emotions.

00:03:55.818 --> 00:03:59.113
Men have to be cold; women are 
the ones who show their emotions.

00:03:59.530 --> 00:04:02.784
This really hurt me and 
I decided that I would kill myself.

00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:07.956
Eight months after my mother
died, my father remarried.

00:04:08.831 --> 00:04:12.252
Now for the first time, I felt hatred within me

00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:14.420
and hatred towards my father.

00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:16.464
I could not understand how

00:04:16.464 --> 00:04:19.634
after only eight months, he could 
have forgotten his wife, my mother.

00:04:19.926 --> 00:04:21.094
I hated my brother,

00:04:21.094 --> 00:04:23.471
who was indifferent. At least 
that's what I thought.

00:04:23.471 --> 00:04:24.806
He was also an alcoholic.

00:04:25.098 --> 00:04:28.518
I hated that woman who came into 
our house, pretending to be my mother.

00:04:30.144 --> 00:04:33.940
June 2nd, 1978.

00:04:34.399 --> 00:04:36.234
It was the first-year anniversary
of my mother's death. 

00:04:36.234 --> 00:04:40.238
I borrowed a gun from a friend. I came home,
my father was watching football (soccer). 

00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:42.699
It was the world cup in Argentina.

00:04:43.449 --> 00:04:45.868
I sat near him wanting to talk,

00:04:45.868 --> 00:04:49.122
but he was totally nervous. He turned
towards me, hit me and yelled at me

00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:50.623
me to go to my room.

00:04:51.291 --> 00:04:56.921
I went to my room, took the gun, pointed
it at my head and pulled the trigger. 

00:04:58.423 --> 00:05:02.468
I woke up in the hospital and overheard
a doctor speaking to someone,

00:05:02.468 --> 00:05:03.886
saying: ...

00:05:04.804 --> 00:05:09.976
'the operation failed. The bullet is in
his head, it cannot be removed,

00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:13.313
and he won't live a long life, he will 
have lots of problems with his head.'

00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:17.191
A few days later, my father and 
stepmother came to the hospital

00:05:18.067 --> 00:05:21.404
and they told me that everything was 
fine and that the bullet had been removed.

00:05:21.404 --> 00:05:25.199
I fell into an even deeper depression,
because I hadn't killed myself.

00:05:25.908 --> 00:05:27.243
When I came out of the hospital,

00:05:27.243 --> 00:05:30.204
I immediately went to alcohol
and started consuming pills.

00:05:30.705 --> 00:05:33.666
I always hung around older people,

00:05:33.875 --> 00:05:35.710
because I felt older.

00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:38.963
All my friends had been smoking 
marihuana and hashish for a long time.

00:05:38.963 --> 00:05:42.633
Every day they would tell me:
'Goran, you're not normal.

00:05:42.633 --> 00:05:45.595
You should start smoking marihuana.

00:05:45.595 --> 00:05:49.057
Marihuana is a natural plant. When you 
smoke it, it's good for your health,

00:05:49.057 --> 00:05:52.894
it develops your brain, you sleep better,
eat better, you're not agressive,

00:05:52.894 --> 00:05:57.065
you have no problems, you just laugh.
There's no withdrawal, no addiction.’

00:05:59.275 --> 00:06:03.946
I started to think that maybe
it wasn't so dangerous. 

00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:07.742
I tried it and then for the following
ten days I didn't smoke any.

00:06:08.326 --> 00:06:10.703
During those ten days I thought to myself:

00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:14.207
'You're a guy with character,

00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:18.378
for ten days you didn't have a need to
light up a joint, everyone is lying,

00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:20.088
marihuana is good.'

00:06:20.421 --> 00:06:22.548
After ten days, I lit another joint

00:06:22.882 --> 00:06:25.843
and just like that the day came when 
I would smoke it from morning until night

00:06:25.843 --> 00:06:26.761
every day.

00:06:27.011 --> 00:06:28.846
However, what happened was

00:06:29.555 --> 00:06:31.599
that one day I woke
up in the hospital.

00:06:31.599 --> 00:06:33.601
My head was injured and blooded...

00:06:33.601 --> 00:06:36.938
the doctors did some 
tests and diagnosed me

00:06:36.938 --> 00:06:38.231
with epilepsy.

00:06:40.733 --> 00:06:42.527
When I developed that disorder,

00:06:42.527 --> 00:06:45.738
I fell into an even deeper depression
because I was embarrassed.

00:06:45.738 --> 00:06:47.865
I knew I had to change my life,

00:06:47.865 --> 00:06:48.866
but how?

00:06:48.866 --> 00:06:51.577
My father was always at sea working,
my brother was drunk every day. 

00:06:51.577 --> 00:06:54.914
My stepmother was afraid of me. 
I was agressive and I directed

00:06:54.914 --> 00:06:56.707
all the blame towards her.

00:06:57.959 --> 00:06:59.836
Thank God for my friends

00:07:00.628 --> 00:07:02.130
who talked me

00:07:03.005 --> 00:07:04.966
into trying heroin.

00:07:04.966 --> 00:07:08.219
They told me: 'Goran, you'll solve
all your problems with heroin.'

00:07:08.678 --> 00:07:11.431
I was convinced that my 
life couldn't get any worse.

00:07:11.681 --> 00:07:15.601
One day I told myself: 'Let me try heroin,
maybe things will be better'.

00:07:16.894 --> 00:07:19.021
At the moment when you try heroin,

00:07:19.021 --> 00:07:22.775
the feeling that comes
into your head is great.

00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:27.989
At the beginning it was good. 
A little money and a little heroin.

00:07:27.989 --> 00:07:31.409
As time went by, every 
day I needed more money.

00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:35.955
I started stealing cars, breaking into homes,
apartments, restaurants, stealing wallets.

00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:39.333
I started doing things which
I was sure I would never do.

00:07:40.001 --> 00:07:42.170
Can you imagine the paradox.

00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:47.758
My poor father worked his whole life
and brought home money and material goods.

00:07:47.758 --> 00:07:51.053
In one month, I stole and 
sold everything he owned.

00:07:51.053 --> 00:07:53.139
He was overcome by panic.

00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:57.977
One day he called me crying: 'Goran, my son

00:07:59.061 --> 00:08:00.480
you have a big problem.

00:08:01.689 --> 00:08:05.318
Please, let's talk about getting you help.'

00:08:06.027 --> 00:08:07.570
I looked at him

00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:09.739
 and said: 'Are you normal?!

00:08:09.739 --> 00:08:11.449
Now you want to sit and talk.

00:08:11.449 --> 00:08:13.284
I've been waiting for you to talk
with me for twenty years, 

00:08:13.284 --> 00:08:15.411
and now it's too late.'

00:08:16.370 --> 00:08:18.289
That was in the eighties,

00:08:18.289 --> 00:08:19.332
during communism.

00:08:19.332 --> 00:08:23.586
There were no counseling centers, no rehab
communities. There wasn't anything.

00:08:23.586 --> 00:08:25.588
My father didn't know where to look for help,

00:08:26.047 --> 00:08:27.507
so he went to the police.

00:08:28.716 --> 00:08:29.634
One morning,

00:08:29.634 --> 00:08:31.260
policemen entered my room,

00:08:31.260 --> 00:08:35.515
brought heroin and threw it near my head
and accused me of being a dealer.

00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:36.724
'Now we're going to lock you up'.

00:08:38.643 --> 00:08:40.102
Their reasoning was logical:

00:08:40.102 --> 00:08:44.315
if they lock me up for five, six months, 
perhaps I'll see that I am on the wrong path.

00:08:44.315 --> 00:08:45.775
Maybe I'll change.

00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:47.527
However, what happened

00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:49.862
in jail was the opposite. 
I learned how to steal better,

00:08:49.862 --> 00:08:52.031
how to mix drugs better 
to increase its quantity. 

00:08:52.031 --> 00:08:55.409
When I got out of prison, I left
smarter than when I went in.

00:08:56.452 --> 00:08:59.830
In prison there's just as many drugs,
alcohol, and pills, as on the outside.

00:08:59.830 --> 00:09:03.334
Being in prison made 
me a hundred times worse,

00:09:04.835 --> 00:09:06.671
so my life agony continued.

00:09:06.671 --> 00:09:08.548
My father was searching for help everywhere.

00:09:10.007 --> 00:09:12.718
One day a friend of my 
father's told him: 'Marko,

00:09:13.886 --> 00:09:15.680
your son Goran is a sick boy.

00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:17.723
When someone is sick,
they go to the doctor.

00:09:17.723 --> 00:09:20.601
You need to lock Goran up
in a psychiatric institution. 

00:09:20.601 --> 00:09:23.688
Psychiatrists are smart, 
highly educated people.

00:09:23.688 --> 00:09:26.899
Nobody will be able to 
help him, other than a doctor.’

00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:29.527
My whole family was happy

00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:32.321
 and started to pressure me to
go to a psychiatric institution.

00:09:32.321 --> 00:09:34.657
I didn't want to go,

00:09:34.657 --> 00:09:37.743
but I had problems with the courts,
as well as the police.

00:09:37.743 --> 00:09:39.161
So finally, I had to go.

00:09:39.537 --> 00:09:42.623
Two days before I was to go,

00:09:42.623 --> 00:09:44.166
I organized everything.

00:09:44.792 --> 00:09:47.878
In Split, the psychiatric institution 
is on the ground floor.

00:09:47.878 --> 00:09:49.255
I had a bed

00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:53.342
and all day I would watch TV 
and joke with the other patients.

00:09:53.342 --> 00:09:55.136
The doctors gave me pills,

00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:57.555
my friends would come
every day and through

00:09:57.555 --> 00:09:59.599
my window, they'd throw
me drugs and alcohol. 

00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:01.851
It was great, like a vacation.

00:10:02.393 --> 00:10:06.439
One night my friends came, and I escaped 
in my pajamas, to a discotheque. 

00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:11.110
Here, it was written 'Psychiatry'. 
There I danced, drank sang

00:10:11.110 --> 00:10:13.362
The police arrived and gave me a beating.

00:10:14.113 --> 00:10:17.074
They returned me to the hospital and 
the doctors went crazy, they didn't know

00:10:17.074 --> 00:10:18.909
what to do with me, because
I disturbed everything there. 

00:10:18.909 --> 00:10:21.871
In the end, of course, they threw me out.

00:10:23.664 --> 00:10:25.750
I got another chance outside,
but it was even worse.

00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:27.793
At home, the police and the ambulance
were visiting my house every day.

00:10:27.793 --> 00:10:30.755
We were fighting, my brother 
was drunk, it was hell. 

00:10:38.971 --> 00:10:42.725
One day, another one of my
father's friends told him:

00:10:42.725 --> 00:10:44.352
'Marko,

00:10:44.352 --> 00:10:47.313
I have been thinking about your 
problem with your son, for a long time.

00:10:47.313 --> 00:10:49.815
You need to find Goran a job.'

00:10:50.566 --> 00:10:53.402
Again, logical reasoning, they thought: 

00:10:53.402 --> 00:10:56.656
'Goran will have to wake 
up early every morning

00:10:56.656 --> 00:10:59.533
and work for eight hours'.

00:10:59.533 --> 00:11:04.372
'He'll get tired and when he's tired, 
he'll have no time for stupidities.

00:11:04.372 --> 00:11:09.543
He'll be with normal people. Step 
by step, he'll have to change.'

00:11:10.294 --> 00:11:11.629
Everyone was happy,

00:11:11.629 --> 00:11:13.589
except for me, of course.

00:11:13.589 --> 00:11:15.257
They started pressuring me to go to work.

00:11:15.257 --> 00:11:17.468
However, I didn't want to do that, 
stealing was easier for me.

00:11:18.177 --> 00:11:19.804
When everyone saw that I refused,

00:11:19.804 --> 00:11:21.806
all my relatives got together and told me: 

00:11:21.806 --> 00:11:22.431
'Listen,

00:11:24.475 --> 00:11:27.436
either you go to work or you're on the street!'.

00:11:32.733 --> 00:11:33.651
I had to choose.

00:11:35.236 --> 00:11:39.240
When it came time to choose between the
two evils, I chose the lesser of the two.

00:11:40.032 --> 00:11:41.242
I went to work.

00:11:47.289 --> 00:11:49.667
My father found me a job in 
the company where he worked. 

00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:52.586
It was a warehouse

00:11:52.586 --> 00:11:55.214
where they had all kinds of 
products for seamen and boats.

00:11:55.214 --> 00:11:57.425
All my father's friends worked there

00:11:58.092 --> 00:12:01.512
and they told him: 'Marko don't 
worry about anything. 

00:12:01.512 --> 00:12:04.265
You just bring Goran.

00:12:04.265 --> 00:12:10.771
We'll take care of him. We'll even 
give him a beating if necessary.

00:12:10.771 --> 00:12:14.608
We'll give him so much work 
that it'll come out of his ears.

00:12:18.112 --> 00:12:19.572
I started to work;

00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:22.742
however it became apparent that 
it was the biggest mistake

00:12:22.742 --> 00:12:24.160
my father could have made.

00:12:24.535 --> 00:12:27.955
I stole half the warehouse and 
sold everything that could

00:12:27.955 --> 00:12:30.291
be sold. I also borrowed money 
from co-workers and never 

00:12:30.291 --> 00:12:31.542
paid anyone back.

00:12:31.542 --> 00:12:34.503
One day, I got angry at the manager 
and chased him with a knife

00:12:34.503 --> 00:12:36.005
round the warehouse.

00:12:37.131 --> 00:12:39.717
They saw that I was a complete idiot

00:12:42.595 --> 00:12:43.763
and they fired me.

00:12:44.847 --> 00:12:46.015
That was the end of that.

00:12:47.266 --> 00:12:49.643
One day I came home
drunk and on a downer.

00:12:49.643 --> 00:12:53.022
I asked my father for money 
and he got angry and hit me.

00:12:53.022 --> 00:12:54.565
We started fighting.

00:12:54.565 --> 00:12:55.983
My father weighed 120 kg.

00:12:55.983 --> 00:12:58.444
I realized that my father was going 
to give me a good beating, so I grabbed

00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.404
a knife and stabbed him in the stomach.

00:13:00.821 --> 00:13:02.823
My father ended up in the 
hospital and I ended up in jail.

00:13:02.823 --> 00:13:04.450
I was angry

00:13:05.159 --> 00:13:06.452
because it was his fault.

00:13:07.787 --> 00:13:10.873
If he had only given me money, I would 
have taken drugs, and nothing would

00:13:10.873 --> 00:13:11.957
have happened.

00:13:11.957 --> 00:13:16.378
As soon as I got out of jail, without even
a little remorse, I wanted to return home

00:13:16.378 --> 00:13:18.506
like nothing had ever happened.

00:13:18.506 --> 00:13:22.051
Today, when I think about it, the worst 
thing that could happen to someone

00:13:22.051 --> 00:13:25.012
is for them to lose their
conscience, as I did then.

00:13:25.930 --> 00:13:27.765
I came home, but the door was locked.

00:13:29.099 --> 00:13:31.519
Behind the door my father said:
'Listen son. 

00:13:32.186 --> 00:13:35.314
Between your family and the 
street, you chose the street.

00:13:35.314 --> 00:13:37.983
Live on the streets with your friends.

00:13:37.983 --> 00:13:40.236
If one day you decide to change your life,

00:13:40.236 --> 00:13:42.571
come back and we'll help you.' 

00:13:43.864 --> 00:13:47.243
At that moment the hatred 
I had for my family

00:13:47.243 --> 00:13:49.578
increased a million times,

00:13:49.578 --> 00:13:53.833
because I couldn't come to understand
how they dared to throw me out of the house.

00:13:55.042 --> 00:13:59.547
I spat on the door and started to swear:

00:14:00.047 --> 00:14:02.091
'I'm leaving and you'll never see me again.'

00:14:03.467 --> 00:14:06.428
For nine years, after that day, 
I lived on the streets like a bum.

00:14:06.428 --> 00:14:09.890
Those nine years were a disaster.

00:14:09.890 --> 00:14:13.394
When you have money, when you
have drugs, you have friends.

00:14:13.769 --> 00:14:16.605
I came to the point where even if 
I had money and drugs, nobody

00:14:16.605 --> 00:14:17.773
wanted to be around me.

00:14:17.773 --> 00:14:20.734
I looked so ugly and behaved so abnormally.

00:14:21.777 --> 00:14:25.823
In the latter part of my life on the streets, 
an irrational fear began to grow inside me,

00:14:26.699 --> 00:14:29.952
which I cannot even describe to you. 
Those fears drove me crazy,

00:14:29.952 --> 00:14:30.995
I feared everything.

00:14:31.745 --> 00:14:35.374
In those moments, not one drug, or 
one pill, could have calmed me down.

00:14:35.374 --> 00:14:38.002
The only thing that calmed
me down, was my blood.

00:14:38.002 --> 00:14:41.839
I would cut myself and with an empty
syringe I would draw my blood out, 

00:14:41.839 --> 00:14:44.466
and then drink it and
rub it all over myself.

00:14:44.466 --> 00:14:46.176
That would give me some kind of peace.

00:14:46.969 --> 00:14:48.178
The last time they locked me up,

00:14:48.679 --> 00:14:52.433
they saw that I wasn't normal, so
they brought me a neuropsychiatrist,

00:14:52.641 --> 00:14:55.311
who diagnosed me as a: schizophrenic

00:14:56.353 --> 00:14:58.397
and I ended up in a mental institution

00:14:58.731 --> 00:14:59.815
in Popovača.

00:15:04.695 --> 00:15:09.116
When I came there, I immediately 
received treatment for my disorder,

00:15:09.909 --> 00:15:11.660
and I calmed down.

00:15:16.206 --> 00:15:17.416
One morning,

00:15:17.416 --> 00:15:20.377
I was sitting at a table in the ward

00:15:21.211 --> 00:15:23.255
and I asked myself, what am I doing here?

00:15:23.255 --> 00:15:25.007
I was a common drug addict

00:15:25.007 --> 00:15:28.093
placed in a ward full of murderers.

00:15:28.093 --> 00:15:29.011
Why?

00:15:29.762 --> 00:15:33.474
While in the Remetinec jail, I was waiting 
transport to the mental institution,

00:15:34.892 --> 00:15:37.311
this was right at the start 
of the Homeland War,

00:15:39.855 --> 00:15:42.232
and the authorities had their hands 
full with many problems, nevertheless,

00:15:44.568 --> 00:15:47.112
I ended up back in the psych
ward with two other guys.

00:15:47.488 --> 00:15:50.157
'My God, I can't stay here.

00:15:50.157 --> 00:15:52.117
They'll kill me within two days.

00:15:52.117 --> 00:15:53.535
I have to escape'.

00:15:53.994 --> 00:15:56.747
So then I analyzed the situation.

00:15:56.747 --> 00:15:58.082
An opportunity presented itself,

00:15:58.082 --> 00:16:01.710
I stole money from a fellow
patient and escaped.

00:16:03.462 --> 00:16:05.172
Obviously, I considered myself smart

00:16:08.842 --> 00:16:11.053
and I had devised a plan in my head.

00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:13.222
I would return to Split,

00:16:13.222 --> 00:16:17.434
take drugs, go fight in the war, Croatia
would win the war and there would

00:16:17.434 --> 00:16:19.103
be a change in government.

00:16:19.478 --> 00:16:20.771
And I would be a free man.

00:16:20.771 --> 00:16:22.189
So simple.

00:16:23.065 --> 00:16:24.233
I'm smart.

00:16:24.775 --> 00:16:28.153
I returned to Split, took some drugs and 
one morning I went to the military barracks.

00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:31.573
I went inside and two 
soldiers looked at me.

00:16:31.573 --> 00:16:33.325
One said to me: 
'Where do you think you're going?'

00:16:33.325 --> 00:16:35.119
So I replied: 'What do you mean,
where am I going? I'm Croatian,

00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:36.578
I'm going to fight and defend my country.'

00:16:36.578 --> 00:16:38.455
The other soldier then said to me:

00:16:38.455 --> 00:16:42.292
'Please turn around and get 
out of here, if not I'll break your legs.'

00:16:44.420 --> 00:16:47.923
Now you all see me tonight at 90 kg,

00:16:48.590 --> 00:16:51.719
but back then I didn't even weigh 60 kg,

00:16:51.719 --> 00:16:53.178
all skin and bones,

00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:57.558
and if they would have 
given me a Kalashnikov,

00:16:57.558 --> 00:17:00.686
I would have definitely sold it at the first 
street corner or exchanged it for some heroin. 

00:17:00.686 --> 00:17:03.647
I'm sure I wasn't the first drug 
addict to have visited that barrack.

00:17:04.273 --> 00:17:07.067
I continued with my life.

00:17:07.943 --> 00:17:11.739
The police had issued an arrest 
warrant for me and they caught me.

00:17:13.115 --> 00:17:14.533
They put me in their van

00:17:14.533 --> 00:17:16.243
and brought me back 
to the mental institution.

00:17:17.161 --> 00:17:20.122
There were two technicians, which
I will never forget,

00:17:21.331 --> 00:17:23.542
because they beat me like an ox.

00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:25.294
They restrained me,

00:17:25.294 --> 00:17:29.173
laid me on a bed and tied
my legs to the bed posts.

00:17:29.173 --> 00:17:31.842
I was tied up like a Zagreb salami

00:17:32.718 --> 00:17:35.679
and they put me in the room of the 
patient, from whom I had stolen money... 

00:17:36.388 --> 00:17:38.223
and he had murdered four people.

00:17:38.932 --> 00:17:41.894
They had intentionally done 
that as a punishment. 

00:17:42.811 --> 00:17:47.399
I had stolen his money, because I was smart
and I was sure I would never return there.

00:17:47.399 --> 00:17:48.817
Everything had been planned.

00:17:49.485 --> 00:17:51.987
I laid tied to my bed.

00:17:51.987 --> 00:17:55.407
He sat on his bed across from 
me, and this went on for five days.

00:17:55.407 --> 00:18:01.288
That murderer sat on his bed, smoked 
cigarettes, and looked at me in the eyes.

00:18:01.288 --> 00:18:04.666
For five days, and he didn't 
speak one single word to me.

00:18:04.666 --> 00:18:08.212
He just stared at me and 
that mentally, was killing me. 

00:18:08.212 --> 00:18:12.883
When someone doesn't speak, you 
don't know what they're thinking.

00:18:13.383 --> 00:18:16.053
Every time he got up from his bed,

00:18:16.053 --> 00:18:20.099
my eyes would turn over, because
I thought he was going to kill me.

00:18:21.183 --> 00:18:24.603
You can all laugh now, but it
wasn't so funny to me then. 

00:18:25.479 --> 00:18:27.272
The fifth day, he looked at me

00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:29.775
and he spoke to me:

00:18:30.400 --> 00:18:32.277
'Listen you little sh*t

00:18:33.487 --> 00:18:35.072
do you know who I am?

00:18:36.907 --> 00:18:39.868
do you know what I have done?
And what I could do to you?

00:18:40.452 --> 00:18:43.997
I've been thinking for five days whether 
I should strangle you like a rabbit or not.

00:18:45.082 --> 00:18:46.834
However, when I think about it a little better,

00:18:46.834 --> 00:18:49.795
you were brave enough to steal my money.

00:18:50.546 --> 00:18:51.964
Well done!'

00:18:55.634 --> 00:18:58.053
It was the nicest moment of my life.

00:18:58.345 --> 00:19:01.306
Later on, he became my friend.
Drago was a good guy.

00:19:02.266 --> 00:19:05.227
 I could write a whole book about 
that Popovača mental institution.

00:19:05.227 --> 00:19:07.437
Over there, everything functioned
when they had medication, 

00:19:08.230 --> 00:19:11.066
but often there was no medication, 
they would give us replacement drugs,

00:19:11.066 --> 00:19:12.067
which wasn't often,

00:19:12.067 --> 00:19:13.777
so it was a circus.

00:19:23.745 --> 00:19:24.955
The main doctor,

00:19:24.955 --> 00:19:28.250
primarius Milivoj Koludrović 
called me into his office

00:19:29.418 --> 00:19:31.837
and told me: 'Goran, tomorrow
you will be released. 

00:19:33.213 --> 00:19:38.260
You make one more wrong move,
and I will personally bring you back here. 

00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:40.971
You'll never get out again.

00:19:40.971 --> 00:19:42.347
You will die here.

00:19:42.347 --> 00:19:46.768
I promise you that, and now think about
what you're going to do with your life.'

00:19:47.477 --> 00:19:51.773
I thought to myself: 
'My God, this guy is not normal!'

00:19:53.525 --> 00:19:55.068
He never forgave me 
for escaping his institution.

00:19:55.068 --> 00:19:56.737
He always made problems for me.

00:19:56.737 --> 00:19:59.698
I didn't have the courage, or the 
will to return there ever again. 

00:20:00.032 --> 00:20:01.909
I thought about what I would do now

00:20:02.534 --> 00:20:03.827
and it came to me

00:20:03.827 --> 00:20:08.665
You idiot, you have to change your life.
Change your life and everything will be fine.

00:20:12.920 --> 00:20:14.963
So I decided to return 
to Split and the first door 

00:20:16.131 --> 00:20:18.217
which I knocked on, was that of my dealer.

00:20:18.217 --> 00:20:21.803
I took some heroin. The next 
afternoon, I continued my old ways,

00:20:23.472 --> 00:20:26.433
but as time went on I couldn't sleep anymore

00:20:27.392 --> 00:20:30.354
I would carry the same sandwich
in my pocket for twenty days.

00:20:30.354 --> 00:20:32.064
That was all the food I had.

00:20:32.064 --> 00:20:34.816
I was full of open wounds.

00:20:34.816 --> 00:20:38.403
You cannot imagine the stench
and smell coming from me, 

00:20:38.403 --> 00:20:40.489
or that a human could even smell like that.

00:20:40.489 --> 00:20:46.328
When I would get on the city bus,
everyone would run out at the next stop, 

00:20:46.328 --> 00:20:49.790
so I always had a place to sit, because
everyone would run away from me. 

00:20:50.540 --> 00:20:53.502
How many times I would sit like 
this, against a wall, bunched up.

00:20:53.502 --> 00:20:57.297
People would pass by me and spit on me.

00:20:57.297 --> 00:20:59.758
They would beat me with their fists
and legs, they would shout that

00:20:59.758 --> 00:21:02.219
 should be killed, because I was 
poison for their children.

00:21:02.761 --> 00:21:04.554
It was all the same to me.

00:21:04.554 --> 00:21:07.516
I was just waiting for the 
moment when I would die.

00:21:07.933 --> 00:21:11.645
For me, death was my salvation.
Life for me was only suffering.

00:21:11.770 --> 00:21:14.731
Often, I would drink a bottle 
of vodka, swallow a box of pills 

00:21:15.524 --> 00:21:18.360
and I would inject myself with heroin
I would be in a coma for a few days,

00:21:18.360 --> 00:21:20.404
but I would always wake up.

00:21:20.404 --> 00:21:22.656
Once I woke up, and it was summer.

00:21:22.656 --> 00:21:24.908
My mouth was full of flies and ants.

00:21:25.534 --> 00:21:26.952
I was given advice

00:21:26.952 --> 00:21:28.370
on how to cut my veins.

00:21:28.370 --> 00:21:30.747
My dear friends, veins are not cut like this,

00:21:30.747 --> 00:21:33.709
they are supposed to be cut 
lengthwise, then you have to die.

00:21:34.209 --> 00:21:38.463
I'm not sure if you remember 
those old razors from the old days.

00:21:40.132 --> 00:21:45.304
It doesn't matter. One day I found 
one of those razors on the ground.

00:21:46.555 --> 00:21:49.516
I took it, and when I took a closer look at it, 

00:21:49.850 --> 00:21:52.769
it was rusted and dirty.

00:21:52.769 --> 00:21:57.065
Then I was afraid of getting an infection 
because you have to think of your health.

00:21:58.817 --> 00:22:01.778
If I'm already going to die, I going
to die healthy, not sick.

00:22:02.696 --> 00:22:04.197
Makes sense right?

00:22:04.781 --> 00:22:06.950
I looked at it like this and said:

00:22:06.950 --> 00:22:09.911
'Oh my God, I need to disinfect it.'

00:22:13.582 --> 00:22:15.042
I disinfected it.

00:22:16.710 --> 00:22:20.964
I was sitting on a bench and
did this. Let me show you

00:22:21.465 --> 00:22:25.344
I put my left arm tightly between my knees,

00:22:25.344 --> 00:22:28.305
 jabbed the razor into my skin and dragged it.

00:22:29.765 --> 00:22:32.184
Then a large hole opened up in 
my arm, which I could have

00:22:32.184 --> 00:22:33.393
put my whole fist into.

00:22:35.562 --> 00:22:38.523
Blood was flowing the whole time

00:22:38.523 --> 00:22:41.485
and I started to become dizzy.

00:22:41.485 --> 00:22:43.612
The only thought I had was: 

00:22:44.363 --> 00:22:46.907
„Thank you Jesus! It's over.“

00:22:47.866 --> 00:22:49.201
Then I fainted.

00:22:49.576 --> 00:22:51.161
I woke up in a hospital.

00:22:53.080 --> 00:22:56.041
How pathetic, I couldn't even kill myself.

00:22:59.336 --> 00:23:00.420
One night

00:23:02.589 --> 00:23:03.632
in February,

00:23:03.632 --> 00:23:05.008
I was in a partially demolished house,

00:23:06.218 --> 00:23:09.721
sitting like a dog on a piece of carton,

00:23:10.097 --> 00:23:12.224
a small candle lit.

00:23:13.809 --> 00:23:15.644
At one point

00:23:15.644 --> 00:23:17.437
I started thinking

00:23:19.398 --> 00:23:22.109
about my family, my childhood.

00:23:23.235 --> 00:23:26.196
The more I thought about it,
the more pain I felt in my chest.

00:23:27.155 --> 00:23:30.117
I finally concluded 
that nobody was to blame.

00:23:30.575 --> 00:23:34.955
I was to blame for everything
that had happened in my life. 

00:23:35.330 --> 00:23:37.290
My whole life I had blamed other people,

00:23:37.290 --> 00:23:38.875
especially my family,

00:23:38.875 --> 00:23:41.837
to justify the evil I was doing.

00:23:43.004 --> 00:23:48.009
When I realized that I was an idiot
that ruined his own life,

00:23:49.261 --> 00:23:52.222
I started crying and praying the Hail Mary.

00:23:53.056 --> 00:23:58.145
I felt hatred towards Jesus, Mary,
the Church, priests and believers like you.

00:23:58.145 --> 00:24:00.814
This type of hatred you cannot even imagine.

00:24:01.440 --> 00:24:05.861
The Hail Mary prayer stayed in my mind
from the time when I was young

00:24:05.861 --> 00:24:09.406
and my parents forced me
to attend religion classes.

00:24:09.906 --> 00:24:13.034
I was suprised that I only 
remembered the Hail Mary.

00:24:13.952 --> 00:24:18.206
All night I cried and 
prayed saying: „Our Lady,

00:24:18.206 --> 00:24:24.838
please take me up to you or give 
me your hand to help me change my life

00:24:24.838 --> 00:24:29.843
I'm tired of everything, do what you 
want with me, but I can't do this anymore.

00:24:31.970 --> 00:24:33.555
I spent all night like that.

00:24:35.265 --> 00:24:38.226
A few days later, I was 
sitting on a park bench,

00:24:38.727 --> 00:24:41.688
early in the morning, it was cold.
Alone like a dog.

00:24:46.193 --> 00:24:49.362
Suddenly, a lady walked into the park.

00:24:53.783 --> 00:24:56.077
It was very odd that some woman
would come into this park.

00:24:56.495 --> 00:24:59.122
I was looking at her 
and she was staring back.

00:24:59.122 --> 00:25:01.917
I kept thinking, I hope she's
not coming towards me. 

00:25:05.754 --> 00:25:08.715
Of course, that wasn't Our Lady.
Don't think that I saw Her.

00:25:16.806 --> 00:25:18.225
She walked in front of me

00:25:18.475 --> 00:25:19.351
and said

00:25:20.352 --> 00:25:21.436
good morning

00:25:24.022 --> 00:25:27.442
she said: 'I have a problem. 
Can you please help me?'.

00:25:28.318 --> 00:25:31.655
When she said that she had a 
problem, I thought I'd go crazy.

00:25:42.707 --> 00:25:45.418
Woman, do you know how
many problems I have?!

00:25:46.044 --> 00:25:47.212
Who was going to help me?

00:25:47.212 --> 00:25:53.343
Woman, get lost, and take
your problems with you, 

00:25:53.343 --> 00:25:55.720
I don't care for you or your problem.

00:25:56.388 --> 00:25:57.973
She got a little scared

00:25:58.431 --> 00:26:01.935
and said: 'Don't...please. I'm looking
for a young man, they call him Ćuke'.

00:26:02.936 --> 00:26:03.770
That was me,

00:26:06.147 --> 00:26:07.732
but I didn’t know who she was,

00:26:07.732 --> 00:26:09.276
or what I could have done.

00:26:09.276 --> 00:26:12.988
I was thinking about telling her that it 
has me, but maybe she'll start yelling,

00:26:13.238 --> 00:26:16.491
people will come and 
they will call the police

00:26:16.491 --> 00:26:17.534
they'll lock me up again.

00:26:17.909 --> 00:26:19.995
On the other hand, I was curious.

00:26:20.412 --> 00:26:22.205
I was in an odd situation,

00:26:25.250 --> 00:26:28.211
so I looked around and there
wasn't anybody nearby. 

00:26:29.129 --> 00:26:30.463
I told her that I was Ćuke.

00:26:31.381 --> 00:26:36.886
She lifted her head and said: “Thank 
you Mother Mary for helping me find him.”

00:26:37.679 --> 00:26:43.518
And I was thinking this lady is insane.

00:26:45.562 --> 00:26:47.522
She took me under the arm

00:26:47.981 --> 00:26:50.942
and said: 'please, let's take a walk'.

00:26:51.651 --> 00:26:54.321
With all that was going on in my life, 
as if I had nothing better to do, but to

00:26:54.321 --> 00:26:56.489
take a walk with some 
old lady around the park.

00:26:56.489 --> 00:26:59.826
However, it came to me: 'Shut up
you idiot, she needs you'.

00:26:59.826 --> 00:27:02.495
Since she needs you, you're 
going to ask her money and 

00:27:02.495 --> 00:27:03.788
he is going to give it to you

00:27:03.788 --> 00:27:06.291
and that was the only reason
I agreed to go with her

00:27:06.291 --> 00:27:07.375
and she gave me money

00:27:09.044 --> 00:27:10.170
and then she started

00:27:10.795 --> 00:27:11.838
her story.

00:27:12.297 --> 00:27:15.634
She said she was the mother of 
a drug addict who ended up in jail.

00:27:16.426 --> 00:27:19.846
That woman with the help of the courts
made an agreement that her son

00:27:19.846 --> 00:27:23.224
will serve out his sentence in the 
Cenacolo Drug Rehabilitation Community.

00:27:26.061 --> 00:27:29.648
She then asked her son if he had a
friend that he wanted her to help,

00:27:30.482 --> 00:27:33.526
and he named me.

00:27:33.526 --> 00:27:34.944
But that made no sense,

00:27:34.944 --> 00:27:37.906
because that young man was 10 
years younger than me. 

00:27:37.906 --> 00:27:42.869
The only thing we had in common was that 
we took heroin together twice, in a woodshed.

00:27:42.869 --> 00:27:44.579
That was all. There was no logic to it.

00:27:45.205 --> 00:27:47.082
That is the way this woman found me.

00:27:47.374 --> 00:27:50.210
In a relatively short time, she had an ID card

00:27:50.210 --> 00:27:52.879
and a citizenship document made for me,
because I had no official documents.

00:27:53.129 --> 00:27:55.548
She took me to a bus station in Split

00:27:55.965 --> 00:27:57.842
and bought me a bus ticket.

00:27:58.343 --> 00:27:59.511
She didn''t say anything.

00:28:00.095 --> 00:28:02.472
I looked at her and asked:
'Wait, where am I going?'

00:28:02.972 --> 00:28:06.643
New Caption

00:28:07.102 --> 00:28:09.479
Where am I going? What is that?

00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:13.191
Then she started to explain to me:

00:28:14.442 --> 00:28:15.235
'Goran,

00:28:16.152 --> 00:28:19.114
Medjugorje is a small place 
in Bosnia and Hercegovina. 

00:28:19.114 --> 00:28:21.157
The Virgin Mary appears there.

00:28:21.157 --> 00:28:25.245
The Virgin Mary is waiting for you.
She loves you and is going to help you.

00:28:25.245 --> 00:28:27.414
You have nothing to worry about.'

00:28:28.456 --> 00:28:31.167
I looked at her thinking:

00:28:32.919 --> 00:28:36.965
'I am a schizophrenic, but this woman
is a hundred times crazier than me.'

00:28:43.388 --> 00:28:44.889
Looking at the bus ticket,

00:28:48.601 --> 00:28:49.352
I thought:

00:28:50.812 --> 00:28:53.106
Sleep on the streets of Split

00:28:53.106 --> 00:28:55.316
or the streets in Medjugorje,
it was all the same to me.

00:28:55.942 --> 00:28:58.570
Back then there was no highway.
The distance was 150 kilometers.

00:29:00.780 --> 00:29:01.948
It wasn't far

00:29:02.407 --> 00:29:03.742
and the trip was free.

00:29:03.742 --> 00:29:06.703
I was a bum, I could sleep anywhere.

00:29:06.703 --> 00:29:08.913
I went on this excursion.

00:29:09.914 --> 00:29:12.751
I came to Medjugorje and as
soon as I came off the bus,

00:29:12.751 --> 00:29:16.296
I went to the nearest store. 
I stole two liters of wine and drank it.

00:29:16.671 --> 00:29:18.089
I walked around the place.

00:29:18.089 --> 00:29:20.800
After some time, I came in
front of a gate that read: 

00:29:20.800 --> 00:29:22.177
„Communitta Cenacolo“

00:29:23.553 --> 00:29:27.974
Then I remembered that the woman,
Mrs. Dijana, talked about some community.

00:29:29.267 --> 00:29:33.646
I looked inside and a few guys
saw me. We started talking

00:29:33.646 --> 00:29:36.900
and of course, when they saw this 
„beauty “, they couldn't resist me.

00:29:37.984 --> 00:29:39.444
They took me in immediately,

00:29:40.069 --> 00:29:42.864
which was a miracle, since no one
has ever been admitted into that 

00:29:42.864 --> 00:29:45.533
community high on drugs or in a 
drunken state, as I was at that moment.

00:29:45.533 --> 00:29:48.578
I got in right away and I had no idea why.

00:29:49.621 --> 00:29:51.206
The first month of withdrawal,

00:29:52.123 --> 00:29:55.251
that was the worst period of my life.

00:29:55.752 --> 00:29:59.172
There were no pills, no alcohol,
no cigarettes, no newspapers,

00:29:59.172 --> 00:30:02.634
no television, just hard work, and prayer.

00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:04.552
If I didn't die then, I wasn't going to.

00:30:06.554 --> 00:30:10.809
No one ever died from withdrawal 
and neither did I, as you can all see.

00:30:11.810 --> 00:30:13.812
The clothes they removed from me,

00:30:13.812 --> 00:30:16.648
couldn't be washed. 
They had to burn them.

00:30:16.648 --> 00:30:19.901
When Sister Elvira saw how
many open wounds I had, 

00:30:20.360 --> 00:30:23.446
she was afraid I was in 
the final stages of AIDS.

00:30:23.822 --> 00:30:26.282
They immediately had me tested.

00:30:26.282 --> 00:30:27.784
Thank God I didn't have AIDS.

00:30:28.827 --> 00:30:31.329
As time went by, the withdrawal passed.

00:30:31.329 --> 00:30:34.290
Little by little I was recovering.

00:30:35.458 --> 00:30:37.919
The first thing that got on my nerves,

00:30:37.919 --> 00:30:39.587
was that the guys in the community

00:30:39.587 --> 00:30:42.549
prayed three rosaries a day.

00:30:43.007 --> 00:30:45.760
I thought: You guys aren't normal;
I'm not going to be a priest.

00:30:45.760 --> 00:30:47.470
I don't have a problem with prayer,

00:30:47.470 --> 00:30:50.640
I have a problem with drugs, alcohol,
and pills. What does prayer have

00:30:50.640 --> 00:30:51.766
to do with those issues?

00:30:52.559 --> 00:30:55.895
One guy asked me: 
'Are you going to pray or not?'

00:30:55.895 --> 00:30:58.857
I couldn't be rude, because 
they accepted me right away.

00:30:59.524 --> 00:31:05.613
So I thought: one rosary, 
15-20 minutes. I could handle that. 

00:31:05.613 --> 00:31:08.575
'Alright, I'll do one, but not three'.

00:31:09.325 --> 00:31:14.956
So the guys said: 'Good, you pray one,
and the other two we'll pray for you.'

00:31:15.540 --> 00:31:21.170
I responded: 'Great guys, thanks!
It's important to pray for others'.

00:31:24.465 --> 00:31:27.427
My whole life was logical, hence
why I ended up where I was.

00:31:31.598 --> 00:31:36.185
Now I'll tell you something I haven't 
spoken about, for at least ten years.

00:31:37.312 --> 00:31:38.313
Summer came.

00:31:39.898 --> 00:31:43.735
The main guy in charge came to 
me and handed me a heavy hammer.

00:31:45.069 --> 00:31:46.529
What is it called?

00:31:49.449 --> 00:31:50.992
Those 12 kg hammers.

00:31:51.492 --> 00:31:52.368
A sledgehammer!

00:31:53.786 --> 00:31:57.874
In Medjugorje, in the summer it 
reaches 40-45 degrees Celsius.

00:32:00.585 --> 00:32:03.922
And this guy tells me: 'You're 
going to the quarry to pound rocks.'

00:32:05.006 --> 00:32:08.426
' I replied: 'Not a chance.
Do you see this hot sun?'

00:32:08.426 --> 00:32:10.637
'I won't ruin my health'.

00:32:16.851 --> 00:32:21.147
and he says: 'You're in a work 
group and you have to pound rock.'

00:32:21.940 --> 00:32:26.152
I told him: 'My friend, thanks,
but that, I won't do.'

00:32:27.654 --> 00:32:30.114
He just looked at me and said:
'You won't?' I said: 'I will not.'

00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:33.743
He said: 'Fine, take a chair and sit there.' 

00:32:37.413 --> 00:32:40.083
Another guy comes to me and says: 
'If you won't work,

00:32:40.667 --> 00:32:41.668
we'll work for you.'

00:32:42.001 --> 00:32:44.963
I replied: 'so work if you are fools.'

00:32:46.756 --> 00:32:50.093
It was 50°C and they were
in a hole, pounding rock.

00:32:50.093 --> 00:32:52.679
There were shards flying from 
the rocks, like shrapnel from a grenade.

00:32:52.679 --> 00:32:54.931
They were getting cut all over
and they were full of blood.

00:32:55.473 --> 00:32:58.434
I was sitting in the 
shade on a plastic chair.

00:32:58.434 --> 00:33:00.853
I sat there comfortably and thought:

00:33:00.853 --> 00:33:04.899
'My God, they are insane working,
this is like a concentration camp,

00:33:04.899 --> 00:33:06.526
how could they work in there?'

00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:08.736
After a few days,

00:33:09.320 --> 00:33:11.447
something strange 
started to happen in me.

00:33:12.573 --> 00:33:15.159
Those guys in the hole
were pounding rock,

00:33:15.159 --> 00:33:17.537
they were working hard, 
but everyone was happy.

00:33:17.537 --> 00:33:22.834
Everyone was telling jokes, they 
were laughing, having a great time.

00:33:24.210 --> 00:33:27.880
I wasn't doing anything, just sitting
 on a chair in the shade

00:33:27.880 --> 00:33:32.176
and I was angry, nervous, jealous.
All the evil was on me.

00:33:32.969 --> 00:33:36.597
Then the time came when I said: 
man, who's crazy here? 

00:33:36.597 --> 00:33:38.307
Either those guys who 
are working in the hole,

00:33:38.307 --> 00:33:39.767
or me who isn't doing anything.

00:33:39.767 --> 00:33:41.310
Then I realized

00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:43.229
that I

00:33:43.563 --> 00:33:44.647
was the fool,

00:33:44.647 --> 00:33:46.983
because for the first
time in my life, I saw

00:33:46.983 --> 00:33:49.193
somebody doing something
unconditionally for me,

00:33:49.193 --> 00:33:54.449
and I realized those actions 
spoke stronger than words.

00:33:54.449 --> 00:33:58.870
So I started to be embarassed watching
them work and fill trucks with rock. 

00:33:58.870 --> 00:34:00.872
So I got up and went to work.

00:34:00.872 --> 00:34:02.915
Man, my life turned around just like that.

00:34:04.250 --> 00:34:06.377
By now, I was in the 
community for eleven months,

00:34:07.420 --> 00:34:09.464
and I started to feel a lot of jealousy,

00:34:09.464 --> 00:34:11.924
which turned into hatred

00:34:13.676 --> 00:34:16.179
towards the other guys because
they had family visiting them. 

00:34:16.179 --> 00:34:17.805
Nobody came to visit me.

00:34:17.805 --> 00:34:21.934
Ten years had passed since 
the last contact with my family.

00:34:22.351 --> 00:34:25.730
Nine years on the streets and
one year in the rehab community.

00:34:26.439 --> 00:34:28.107
Daily prayer

00:34:32.862 --> 00:34:35.823
made me outwardly conscious

00:34:37.700 --> 00:34:39.827
and I started to regret 
everything I had done.

00:34:40.495 --> 00:34:42.872
At that point in my life, I would have 
liked to make peace with my family

00:34:42.872 --> 00:34:45.041
and with my father. But how?

00:34:45.041 --> 00:34:46.834
I wanted to write a letter,

00:34:46.834 --> 00:34:48.336
but the guys told me that I couldn't

00:34:48.336 --> 00:34:50.379
and that I had to make penance.

00:34:50.379 --> 00:34:53.591
Without penance, there is no
love and there is no fruit.

00:34:53.591 --> 00:34:56.844
So for penance, they told me to 
wake up at 2 a.m every day, and

00:34:56.844 --> 00:34:59.263
go to the chapel for an hour of prayer,

00:34:59.263 --> 00:35:00.848
on my knees and with faith and conviction.

00:35:00.848 --> 00:35:02.892
They said everything would then be fine.

00:35:03.518 --> 00:35:05.853
But I thought: Who's going
to wake up at 2 a.m?

00:35:06.562 --> 00:35:08.815
Couldn't they think of anything easier?

00:35:09.357 --> 00:35:11.776
As time went on nothing was happening.

00:35:11.776 --> 00:35:13.986
I had a big desire to make
peace with my family. 

00:35:14.821 --> 00:35:17.949
I started waking up at 2 a.m,
I started praying.

00:35:20.701 --> 00:35:25.123
I was sure that I'd die before my 
father would make peace with me.

00:35:29.168 --> 00:35:30.169
Not even

00:35:32.964 --> 00:35:34.674
a month passed,

00:35:34.674 --> 00:35:39.095
when one guy said to me: 'Come with 
me Goran, some pilgrims came from Croatia,

00:35:39.095 --> 00:35:40.555
please show them around
our rehab community.'

00:35:42.807 --> 00:35:45.768
I came there, opened the 
dining room doors to the pilgrims,

00:35:46.269 --> 00:35:49.230
and when I lifted my head
the first face that I saw,

00:35:49.230 --> 00:35:51.023
was that of my father.

00:35:55.611 --> 00:35:59.407
That was the hardest moment of my life.

00:35:59.407 --> 00:36:03.286
That feeling of embarrassment, and guilt.
I cannot describe that feeling to you.

00:36:03.828 --> 00:36:07.623
I remained frozen, with my head down.
I didn't have the courage to look at

00:36:07.623 --> 00:36:09.750
him again, from the 
embarrassment I felt.

00:36:10.168 --> 00:36:12.295
Poor him, he saw 
how difficult it was for me.

00:36:12.295 --> 00:36:15.673
He came to me, hugged me,
and started crying. 

00:36:15.673 --> 00:36:18.634
Then I hugged him 
back and started crying.

00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:22.972
The whole day, we just cried
together. We didn't speak.

00:36:23.431 --> 00:36:26.392
I didn't even know what to say to him.
Do I tell him that I'll be good? 

00:36:26.392 --> 00:36:28.394
I didn't even have the strength
to ask for his forgiveness,

00:36:28.394 --> 00:36:30.688
because I couldn't promise 
him that I would remain sober.

00:36:30.688 --> 00:36:32.106
My whole life, I lied.

00:36:32.106 --> 00:36:34.400
For the first time, I wanted to be
honest towards him and I didn't

00:36:34.400 --> 00:36:36.110
want to give him false hope.

00:36:37.278 --> 00:36:39.572
The only thing I told him when 
he was leaving, was:

00:36:40.698 --> 00:36:41.908
'Listen.

00:36:43.659 --> 00:36:46.621
I destroyed myself and you.

00:36:47.038 --> 00:36:51.751
So I told him: 'Maybe tomorrow 
something will trigger me, in this

00:36:51.751 --> 00:36:55.671
crazy head of mine, to go
back to my old ways,

00:36:55.671 --> 00:36:57.632
but in order to avoid this from happening,

00:36:58.716 --> 00:37:01.219
can you do something for me?

00:37:10.728 --> 00:37:12.355
I am requesting, if you want,

00:37:12.355 --> 00:37:13.898
when you return home,

00:37:13.898 --> 00:37:16.901
that you ask your wife,

00:37:17.652 --> 00:37:19.612
for both of you to start praying

00:37:19.612 --> 00:37:21.280
for my conversion?'

00:37:22.823 --> 00:37:26.953
'Son, what do you think? We have been
praying for you for many years now.'

00:37:27.954 --> 00:37:29.747
Today, looking back,

00:37:30.206 --> 00:37:32.250
everything in my life 
had to be the way it was,

00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:35.586
so that all that hardship would return
my family to prayer and faith.

00:37:35.586 --> 00:37:38.172
Each one of us had 
his way of the Cross,

00:37:38.172 --> 00:37:42.260
so that God could show us
that we had to return to Church.

00:37:42.677 --> 00:37:47.473
All the suffering, all the pain of each
one of us, made sense with God.

00:37:48.933 --> 00:37:51.060
That is how I think about it.

00:37:51.352 --> 00:37:54.188
That encounter with my father 
gave me an even bigger desire

00:37:54.188 --> 00:37:57.024
and hope that I will convert,
and gave me strenght to continue

00:37:57.024 --> 00:37:58.609
in the community, to change. 

00:37:59.193 --> 00:38:02.154
After spending fours years in the community,
I had a desire to leave it. 

00:38:03.656 --> 00:38:06.033
I didn't want to return
to my old life in Split,

00:38:06.075 --> 00:38:08.619
since I felt reborn in Medjugorje.

00:38:08.619 --> 00:38:11.414
But there was a problem, nobody
wanted to give me a job, 

00:38:11.414 --> 00:38:12.581
nobody trusted me.

00:38:12.581 --> 00:38:16.252
What would I do without a job?
Start stealing again? Not a chance.

00:38:16.252 --> 00:38:19.338
I wanted to live honestly, like other
people, but how without a job? 

00:38:20.089 --> 00:38:22.133
I started praying even more

00:38:22.466 --> 00:38:23.884
and Our Lady solved everything.

00:38:24.844 --> 00:38:28.389
I was good friends with the now
deceased Father Slavko Barbarić,

00:38:29.473 --> 00:38:31.392
a franciscan priest who was
a legend in Medjugorje.

00:38:31.392 --> 00:38:33.311
He died up on Križevac mountain.

00:38:33.311 --> 00:38:36.105
He would come to our community
to hear our confessions,

00:38:36.105 --> 00:38:38.149
or Eucharistic adoration and
to celebrate Mass every day

00:38:38.149 --> 00:38:39.608
I was really good with him.

00:38:40.401 --> 00:38:41.986
I told him: 'Father,

00:38:43.571 --> 00:38:46.198
I don't want to be in this rehab 
community for the rest of my life

00:38:46.198 --> 00:38:47.825
and I don't want to return to Split.

00:38:47.825 --> 00:38:50.786
I want to start my life 
over from here, from zero.

00:38:51.120 --> 00:38:53.998
I would like to live here with Our Lady, 

00:38:53.998 --> 00:38:55.583
but nobody trusts me.

00:38:55.583 --> 00:39:00.004
I can't find a job. Please help me find 
something, so that I can start living

00:39:00.004 --> 00:39:02.131
normal life, like other people.'

00:39:02.965 --> 00:39:05.509
He looked at me like
this and said: 'Goran,

00:39:05.509 --> 00:39:07.636
I've been observing you for a while.

00:39:07.636 --> 00:39:11.098
I see that you're a good guy, so 
I'll find you something,

00:39:11.724 --> 00:39:13.642
but you have to be patient.'

00:39:14.310 --> 00:39:15.853
Not even twenty days passed,

00:39:16.562 --> 00:39:20.358
when Father Slavko came to 
my rehab center and told me: 'Goran,

00:39:20.358 --> 00:39:23.986
listen, I have good news for you.

00:39:23.986 --> 00:39:25.154
I have a job for you.

00:39:28.366 --> 00:39:30.576
Don't dare to disappoint me,

00:39:31.577 --> 00:39:35.247
Don't dare to disappoint me,
because I found you a great job.

00:39:35.247 --> 00:39:39.502
Goran, believe me, 
I'll make you a Director.'

00:39:42.004 --> 00:39:45.966
I thought to myself: Man, it was worth
taking drugs, I'll be a Director.

00:39:45.966 --> 00:39:48.427
If I had not taken drugs, I would have
never become a Director. 

00:39:51.597 --> 00:39:53.599
We spoke a little while,

00:39:55.017 --> 00:39:57.645
then he left, and I was alone

00:39:58.521 --> 00:39:59.939
and I thought to myself.

00:40:03.567 --> 00:40:05.778
How will I be a Director
without an education,

00:40:05.778 --> 00:40:07.071
I'm a common ex-drug addict.

00:40:07.071 --> 00:40:10.574
But a priest wouldn't lie, nobody 
should, but especially not a priest.

00:40:10.574 --> 00:40:11.742
I didn't understand what was going on,

00:40:12.743 --> 00:40:14.370
so I went to the parish office

00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:15.996
and found Father Slavko and asked him:

00:40:15.996 --> 00:40:18.290
'What will I be doing as a job?'.

00:40:18.833 --> 00:40:20.334
He said to me:

00:40:20.334 --> 00:40:23.295
'You're going to clean toilets, what
did you think you'd be doing?'. 

00:40:23.879 --> 00:40:27.258
I thought to myself: My Lord, I'm going
to be the toilet cleaning Director!

00:40:29.468 --> 00:40:31.512
For those that have been to Medugorje,

00:40:31.512 --> 00:40:35.224
New Caption

00:40:35.891 --> 00:40:41.397
Men and women's stalls, urinals, what 
can I tell you, work up till here.

00:40:42.398 --> 00:40:48.821
It was great for me. I cleaned, washed,
sang, prayed, got to know people.

00:40:48.821 --> 00:40:51.115
In the washrooms it's always very lively.

00:40:57.913 --> 00:40:59.248
It was good.

00:40:59.248 --> 00:41:00.458
It was great.

00:41:02.334 --> 00:41:03.544
Meanwhile,

00:41:05.296 --> 00:41:06.755
time was passing.

00:41:10.259 --> 00:41:12.678
Every day I became more
and more nervous,

00:41:13.471 --> 00:41:15.890
because I was working every day,

00:41:15.890 --> 00:41:18.309
including Saturdays and
Sundays, along with holidays.

00:41:18.893 --> 00:41:21.020
Every morning I would start at 7 a.m

00:41:21.020 --> 00:41:23.439
and I would finish at 11 p.m. 

00:41:23.439 --> 00:41:26.859
Therefore, I didn't have a free minute.

00:41:26.859 --> 00:41:31.113
 Nuns would bring me breakfast, 
lunch, and supper to my toilet workplace.

00:41:32.031 --> 00:41:33.574
My God...

00:41:34.283 --> 00:41:37.745
Don't get me wrong, I'm not complaining, 

00:41:37.745 --> 00:41:39.079
because on one hand

00:41:39.079 --> 00:41:40.289
it was good,

00:41:40.456 --> 00:41:44.084
I was getting paid, and I didn't have
time to spend my money. 

00:41:44.543 --> 00:41:46.754
I would put all my money aside.

00:41:47.171 --> 00:41:50.466
I didn't pay for the washroom, because
I was the director and obviously,

00:41:50.466 --> 00:41:52.843
directors must have some privileges.

00:41:55.679 --> 00:41:57.598
On one hand it was good,

00:42:00.267 --> 00:42:02.853
however, on the other hand, 
what bothered me

00:42:04.271 --> 00:42:07.233
was that I wanted to find a girlfriend.

00:42:07.399 --> 00:42:10.361
How will I find a girlfriend when 
I spend all day in the washroom.

00:42:12.071 --> 00:42:15.991
This meant that the only option I had left,
was to search for the love of my life

00:42:15.991 --> 00:42:17.826
in a public washroom.

00:42:19.578 --> 00:42:21.413
You all laugh, just laugh.

00:42:28.045 --> 00:42:31.549
You must understand, 
there are two entrances,

00:42:32.716 --> 00:42:33.801
for ladies

00:42:34.635 --> 00:42:35.678
and for gentlemen.

00:42:36.136 --> 00:42:38.806
At that time, when I was the director

00:42:38.806 --> 00:42:42.726
the entrance for the women didn't exist.

00:42:43.185 --> 00:42:45.229
Only the men's entrance existed.

00:42:46.480 --> 00:42:48.649
Everyone would enter 
through the same door

00:42:48.649 --> 00:42:50.568
and separate once inside,

00:42:51.110 --> 00:42:52.695
this is a very important detail.

00:42:53.028 --> 00:42:56.991
It's important, because across from 
the men's entrance, was my director's office.

00:42:57.575 --> 00:42:58.826
It's still there.

00:42:58.826 --> 00:43:03.205
The office has one window. Actually, there 
are two windows, but one is important

00:43:04.290 --> 00:43:05.708
because it has a view of the entrance.

00:43:06.375 --> 00:43:08.335
I spent the whole day behind that window.

00:43:11.589 --> 00:43:13.257
I just watched the girls enter.

00:43:13.549 --> 00:43:16.468
I couldn't care less who paid and
who didn't pay the washroom fee.

00:43:16.468 --> 00:43:18.387
The parish office went 
bankrupt due to my inattention.

00:43:18.387 --> 00:43:20.055
At one point, they didn't even 
have money to buy toilet paper,

00:43:20.055 --> 00:43:22.141
but I just continued 
watching the women enter.

00:43:22.766 --> 00:43:24.310
And God knows

00:43:26.353 --> 00:43:29.315
I saw a lot of pretty girls 
and women enter.

00:43:29.315 --> 00:43:31.025
All women are beautiful, in my opinion.

00:43:32.985 --> 00:43:34.236
One day,

00:43:34.236 --> 00:43:36.363
a young lady walked in,

00:43:39.408 --> 00:43:42.369
and when she passed by me

00:43:44.330 --> 00:43:46.624
it was as if I got struck by lightening.

00:43:53.714 --> 00:43:58.093
At that moment, I knew she
would be my wife one day.

00:43:59.011 --> 00:44:01.305
I saw her for the first time in my life.

00:44:01.305 --> 00:44:03.891
I didn't know anything 
about her, but I only knew:

00:44:03.891 --> 00:44:06.352
'Our Lady put her on my
path, she'll be mine.'

00:44:07.978 --> 00:44:09.480
Now, I was getting even more edgy,

00:44:10.689 --> 00:44:12.149
I felt I couldn't search for her,

00:44:12.149 --> 00:44:15.110
nor investigate who she was
or where she came from.

00:44:15.402 --> 00:44:16.070
I couldn’t,

00:44:16.070 --> 00:44:18.572
because I was too busy working 
from morning until night, every day.

00:44:18.572 --> 00:44:21.742
So I had a big problem, which 
I wouldn't be able to solve by myself.

00:44:21.742 --> 00:44:25.079
In life when you have a problem which
you cannot solve by yourself,

00:44:25.079 --> 00:44:26.622
the only thing you have is

00:44:28.415 --> 00:44:29.541
to pray for answers.

00:44:29.541 --> 00:44:34.838
I started to pray humbly to the 
Holy Spirit, that He descends on

00:44:34.838 --> 00:44:37.716
New Caption

00:44:40.594 --> 00:44:42.262
Not even ten days passed

00:44:42.262 --> 00:44:44.848
When, now deceased, Father 
Ivan Bradvica came to me and said:

00:44:44.848 --> 00:44:47.142
'Goran, you did a good
job in the washrooms,

00:44:47.559 --> 00:44:48.936
you're getting a promotion.'

00:44:50.145 --> 00:44:52.314
My Lady, I love you so much.

00:44:52.856 --> 00:44:53.857
So quick

00:44:54.233 --> 00:44:55.901
and even a promotion.

00:44:56.985 --> 00:44:58.487
I came to the parish office and asked:

00:44:58.487 --> 00:44:59.822
'Father what will I be doing?'

00:44:59.822 --> 00:45:02.950
He said: 'There is a broom.
You'll broom the streets of Medujgorje.'

00:45:06.912 --> 00:45:08.247
I would be working eight hours.

00:45:08.664 --> 00:45:10.457
I would have lots of free time.

00:45:10.457 --> 00:45:11.709
When I prayed,

00:45:12.084 --> 00:45:14.086
I didn't pray for a better job,

00:45:14.086 --> 00:45:15.129
or more money,

00:45:15.129 --> 00:45:17.423
I prayed for free time

00:45:17.423 --> 00:45:19.883
so that I could find out
who that girl was,

00:45:19.883 --> 00:45:20.968
and that's what I got.

00:45:21.135 --> 00:45:23.303
I didn't care about the job.
I would do anything,

00:45:24.012 --> 00:45:26.724
so I immediately went around
and started to inform myself

00:45:26.724 --> 00:45:28.517
about who this girl was,
where she came from.

00:45:28.809 --> 00:45:30.769
There were problems
right from the start

00:45:32.062 --> 00:45:33.480
because I discovered

00:45:33.689 --> 00:45:34.690
that the girl

00:45:36.817 --> 00:45:37.693
was Czech

00:45:38.068 --> 00:45:39.611
and she didn't understand Croatian,

00:45:39.611 --> 00:45:41.447
and she was thirteen 
years younger than me.

00:45:41.739 --> 00:45:43.782
She was a million times 
more attractive than me,

00:45:43.782 --> 00:45:45.701
and she never had a boyfriend.

00:45:45.701 --> 00:45:48.328
She came to Medjugorje
to pray for her calling

00:45:48.328 --> 00:45:50.497
because she wanted
to become a nun.

00:45:51.331 --> 00:45:54.626
Well, that's what I found out,
but I knew that one day,

00:45:54.626 --> 00:45:56.086
she would become my wife.

00:45:59.339 --> 00:46:00.340
Imagine me,

00:46:01.049 --> 00:46:06.221
a drug addict, alcoholic, pill 
popping thief with hepatitis C,

00:46:06.221 --> 00:46:07.639
all cut up with tattoos.

00:46:07.639 --> 00:46:11.435
An epileptic, schizophrenic 
with a bullet stuck in his head,

00:46:13.103 --> 00:46:14.688
and

00:46:14.688 --> 00:46:16.023
the best of all

00:46:16.315 --> 00:46:17.941
when I smiled,

00:46:18.609 --> 00:46:19.860
I had three teeth.

00:46:19.860 --> 00:46:21.904
Two grey and one black

00:46:25.741 --> 00:46:26.867
- what a beauty.

00:46:26.867 --> 00:46:28.702
Who wouldn't want me?

00:46:31.830 --> 00:46:33.165
What a disaster.

00:46:33.832 --> 00:46:36.418
My friends in Medjugorje told me:

00:46:36.960 --> 00:46:40.422
'don't get angry, man, but you're not normal,

00:46:40.422 --> 00:46:42.174
take a look at yourself.

00:46:42.174 --> 00:46:45.260
With your diagnoses, nobody
will ever want you.

00:46:45.260 --> 00:46:47.596
You'll be alone for 
the rest of your life.

00:46:47.596 --> 00:46:49.014
Why are you making 
problems for yourself,

00:46:49.014 --> 00:46:50.891
you can be happy as you are now.'

00:46:53.602 --> 00:46:55.354
But I knew she would be my wife,

00:46:55.938 --> 00:46:57.231
I wasn't stupid

00:46:58.357 --> 00:47:01.068
I knew it wouldn't be that simple,

00:47:01.985 --> 00:47:04.947
so I ran after here like 
a dog for nine months.

00:47:05.781 --> 00:47:07.950
She would yell at me,
tell me that I'm ugly,

00:47:07.950 --> 00:47:09.117
old

00:47:09.117 --> 00:47:10.077
and boring.

00:47:10.077 --> 00:47:11.703
She would humiliate
me in front of others,

00:47:11.703 --> 00:47:13.121
she was mean towards me.

00:47:13.121 --> 00:47:16.083
But, like all loyal dogs,
I followed her around.

00:47:17.209 --> 00:47:19.545
She lived and worked
in a boarding house, 

00:47:19.545 --> 00:47:22.047
so that she could have a free 
room in which she can pray for

00:47:22.047 --> 00:47:23.006
her vocation.

00:47:23.549 --> 00:47:27.094
I quickly became friends with 
the owners of that boarding house.

00:47:28.428 --> 00:47:32.516
I would come there 
with chocolates, gifts and flowers...

00:47:32.516 --> 00:47:35.477
When she would see me, she'd run
to her room and lock the door. 

00:47:36.478 --> 00:47:38.730
Nine months of this, and her feelings
for me didn't move a millimeter. 

00:47:38.730 --> 00:47:39.565
Nothing.

00:47:46.822 --> 00:47:48.991
At one point it came to me.

00:47:49.950 --> 00:47:52.411
You fool, if it's not 
working, change your tactic.

00:47:58.959 --> 00:48:01.962
I was at the boarding house;
Katarina was washing dishes.

00:48:02.671 --> 00:48:04.548
I sat down and said to her: 'Kate,

00:48:04.548 --> 00:48:06.383
my love, listen.

00:48:08.969 --> 00:48:10.429
This is over.

00:48:12.389 --> 00:48:14.850
You know that I just 
returned from Germany.

00:48:15.267 --> 00:48:17.227
Well, I met a girl there.

00:48:17.227 --> 00:48:19.229
That girl now wishes to be with me.

00:48:19.229 --> 00:48:20.814
I am packing my things,

00:48:20.814 --> 00:48:23.025
and in the next few days,
I'm leaving for Hamburg.

00:48:23.358 --> 00:48:24.818
There, I will get married with her

00:48:24.818 --> 00:48:26.111
and make a family,

00:48:26.111 --> 00:48:27.321
children.

00:48:27.321 --> 00:48:29.781
and you continue washing dishes here
in Medjugorje, because you are a fool. 

00:48:29.781 --> 00:48:31.450
There's nothing I can 
do for you, anymore.'

00:48:31.909 --> 00:48:33.577
As I was speaking,

00:48:33.577 --> 00:48:35.454
she threw the dishes

00:48:35.454 --> 00:48:37.205
and started running to her room.

00:48:37.873 --> 00:48:40.834
As she was running, I looked at her 

00:48:40.834 --> 00:48:43.629
and I thought to myself: 'I think there's
going to be something here.'

00:48:44.129 --> 00:48:46.590
I stood up and left.

00:48:48.926 --> 00:48:52.512
During those nine months
of running after Katarina, 

00:48:52.512 --> 00:48:55.933
she got to know me, what kind
of a man I was on the inside. 

00:48:56.433 --> 00:48:58.936
She started to have feelings for me,

00:48:58.936 --> 00:49:01.897
but she was afraid of my past.

00:49:01.897 --> 00:49:05.400
She was sad, because I was leaving 
and we would never see each other again.

00:49:05.651 --> 00:49:08.612
She didn't want us to part that way.

00:49:08.612 --> 00:49:11.365
She wanted to talk, 
open her heart to me,

00:49:11.365 --> 00:49:14.284
talk about her feelings 
and ask for forgiveness.

00:49:14.284 --> 00:49:16.536
But she didn't know whether 
it was God's will for her to do so.

00:49:16.912 --> 00:49:18.956
So she trekked up Križevac Hill.

00:49:20.207 --> 00:49:22.167
She climbed up there, kneeled
at the foot of the cross

00:49:22.876 --> 00:49:24.878
and said: 'My dear Jesus,

00:49:25.963 --> 00:49:27.214
Goran is leaving.

00:49:27.297 --> 00:49:29.508
I'll never see him again.

00:49:29.508 --> 00:49:33.595
I'm sad my Jesus, because you
know how I feel about Goran. 

00:49:34.471 --> 00:49:39.518
But my dear Jesus, I don't know if it 
is Your will that I open my heart to him.

00:49:42.980 --> 00:49:44.898
So let's make an agreement

00:49:45.732 --> 00:49:47.901
to see whether it is Your will or
not for me to open my heart.

00:49:47.901 --> 00:49:49.861
Let's agree on the following:

00:49:50.153 --> 00:49:51.446
if Goran

00:49:51.446 --> 00:49:53.573
comes to me tonight

00:49:53.573 --> 00:49:56.076
and asks me this exact question:

00:49:56.952 --> 00:49:58.745
'is there anything you'd like to tell me?'

00:50:03.667 --> 00:50:06.628
I promise you, without any reservations,
I will consider it to be Your will for me 

00:50:06.628 --> 00:50:10.549
to open my heart to him. This will be 
the only way I tell him everything I feel.

00:50:12.718 --> 00:50:15.554
That evening, I came into a cafe for a coffee.

00:50:15.554 --> 00:50:18.306
I turned my head, and there 
was Katarina with two girlfriends.

00:50:18.306 --> 00:50:21.184
I took a chair right near them.

00:50:21.184 --> 00:50:22.477
I looked at her in the eyes

00:50:22.477 --> 00:50:24.688
and the only thing I said to her, was:
'Kate,

00:50:24.688 --> 00:50:26.314
is there anything you'd like to tell me?'.

00:50:27.774 --> 00:50:30.861
When I asked her that question,

00:50:30.861 --> 00:50:32.821
she began to tremble like this.

00:50:33.947 --> 00:50:37.743
I got scared. I said:

00:50:37.743 --> 00:50:41.580
'Man, there's always an issue 
with you. I asked you a simple question.'

00:50:47.294 --> 00:50:48.962
She was

00:50:48.962 --> 00:50:50.547
 in complete shock.

00:50:51.131 --> 00:50:52.758
She grabbed my hand

00:50:53.175 --> 00:50:56.553
and said: 'Please, let's go 
outside. I want to talk to you.'

00:51:08.482 --> 00:51:09.900
So we went outside

00:51:10.776 --> 00:51:12.110
and she began:

00:51:13.528 --> 00:51:16.073
'I am really sorry that I insulted

00:51:16.073 --> 00:51:17.491
and humiliated you.

00:51:17.491 --> 00:51:19.284
I know you are a good man.

00:51:19.284 --> 00:51:21.328
I have feelings for you,

00:51:21.328 --> 00:51:25.624
but I'm afraid of your past. Now it's
too late for us to start something, 

00:51:25.624 --> 00:51:29.336
since you're leaving for Germany.
We'll never see each other again,

00:51:29.336 --> 00:51:30.545
you have another woman.

00:51:31.213 --> 00:51:33.548
I wish you all the best in life.'

00:51:33.548 --> 00:51:35.008
And she went on

00:51:35.008 --> 00:51:37.302
and on

00:51:38.428 --> 00:51:40.806
I was as quiet as a 
priest during confession.

00:51:45.102 --> 00:51:49.564
One hour she spoke, man,
my head was this big.

00:51:52.234 --> 00:51:54.736
I told her: 'Are you finished yet?

00:51:55.403 --> 00:51:57.239
You're the only one speaking.

00:51:57.697 --> 00:52:00.659
Can I say something? Slow down,

00:52:00.909 --> 00:52:02.452
why are you rushing?

00:52:03.328 --> 00:52:04.496
Katarina,

00:52:04.746 --> 00:52:05.622
wait,

00:52:08.041 --> 00:52:09.793
I have to be honest with you.

00:52:10.168 --> 00:52:13.421
The girl in Germany doesn't
interest me at all.

00:52:13.713 --> 00:52:17.092
I am in love with you, and I want 
to spend the rest of my life with you.

00:52:17.092 --> 00:52:19.261
I love you, is that clear to you?'

00:52:20.011 --> 00:52:21.263
When I said that,

00:52:21.263 --> 00:52:22.556
she got angry,

00:52:24.182 --> 00:52:26.601
because she was sure 
I was going to Germany.

00:52:26.601 --> 00:52:28.520
Now everything had turned around.

00:52:30.605 --> 00:52:31.898
I'm not stupid.

00:52:33.483 --> 00:52:35.527
While Katarina was speaking

00:52:35.777 --> 00:52:38.905
I was quietly listening.

00:52:40.115 --> 00:52:42.742
She opened her heart to
me and told me everything,

00:52:43.743 --> 00:52:48.623
I knew everything now. I knew I had to win 
her over and this was my only chance. 

00:52:49.374 --> 00:52:53.044
And was I very annoying, You can
imagine how relentless I was, 

00:52:53.044 --> 00:52:55.172
when finally she started crying

00:52:55.172 --> 00:52:59.467
and said: 'You liar, you've deceived me.'

00:53:00.635 --> 00:53:03.597
She was thinking about
it, thinking,thinking

00:53:03.680 --> 00:53:05.765
and after a while she said:

00:53:11.271 --> 00:53:12.439
'Let's try.

00:53:13.273 --> 00:53:14.608
But my dear,

00:53:14.983 --> 00:53:16.193
there's no sex,

00:53:16.610 --> 00:53:18.737
you can't even kiss my face,

00:53:19.279 --> 00:53:21.406
you can't even hold my hand

00:53:22.157 --> 00:53:24.910
until the wedding, 

00:53:25.327 --> 00:53:26.661
I said: 'Great!

00:53:27.204 --> 00:53:28.121
Let's do this!'

00:53:30.290 --> 00:53:32.417
We were together fifteen months

00:53:33.001 --> 00:53:37.047
and every now and then I tell her:
'Katarina, please, I'm getting old.

00:53:37.047 --> 00:53:40.008
I want to get married. 
I want a family, children.

00:53:40.008 --> 00:53:41.718
I want to live a normal
life, like other people.

00:53:41.718 --> 00:53:43.762
Don't you want to?
What are we waiting for?

00:53:43.762 --> 00:53:48.266
She told me: 'Relax,
why are you rushing.

00:53:48.266 --> 00:53:52.437
Does this mean you've been 
hiding something from me?'

00:53:58.526 --> 00:54:00.195
Fifteen months

00:54:00.737 --> 00:54:02.239
and I had it 

00:54:02.239 --> 00:54:03.240
up to here.

00:54:06.576 --> 00:54:07.577
That day,

00:54:08.245 --> 00:54:09.829
I told her: 'Kate,

00:54:10.121 --> 00:54:12.707
please sit down. Listen,

00:54:14.542 --> 00:54:16.294
this relationship makes no sense.

00:54:16.294 --> 00:54:18.171
This is what we're going to do,

00:54:18.171 --> 00:54:19.881
whether you agree or not,

00:54:20.757 --> 00:54:21.883
you have two days

00:54:22.676 --> 00:54:23.969
to tell me

00:54:24.219 --> 00:54:25.387
if you wish to marry me.

00:54:25.762 --> 00:54:26.846
If you don't,

00:54:27.347 --> 00:54:28.390
If you don't,

00:54:28.390 --> 00:54:29.474
no problem,

00:54:29.474 --> 00:54:31.059
I won't get angry.

00:54:31.059 --> 00:54:33.853
You can go on 
your merry way then,

00:54:33.853 --> 00:54:35.438
and I'll go my way as well.

00:54:36.356 --> 00:54:37.524
I love you,

00:54:37.691 --> 00:54:39.859
but I will not date
you for ten years.

00:54:40.026 --> 00:54:43.321
If you don't trust me sorry,
but that's your problem. 

00:54:43.321 --> 00:54:47.325
You have two days to tell 
me yes or no and that's it.'

00:54:47.784 --> 00:54:48.660
She was in shock.

00:54:49.786 --> 00:54:51.121
She didn't know what to do.

00:54:51.121 --> 00:54:53.748
On one hand, she wanted 
to get married, she loved me,

00:54:53.748 --> 00:54:56.418
but on the other hand, she had to
have me for the rest of her life,

00:54:56.418 --> 00:54:57.544
along with my past.

00:54:57.544 --> 00:54:59.212
Obviously, she was afraid.

00:55:00.255 --> 00:55:01.756
Where do you think she went?

00:55:06.177 --> 00:55:07.679
She quickly trekked up Križevac hill

00:55:10.557 --> 00:55:13.893
and when she got to the top, she saw
a group of pilgrims from Slovakia

00:55:15.061 --> 00:55:16.146
and she's a Czech.

00:55:16.813 --> 00:55:20.066
Within the group there was a 
priest holding a Bible under his arm.

00:55:20.317 --> 00:55:23.820
She came to him and said: 
'Can you kindly lend me your Bible?'

00:55:24.070 --> 00:55:25.572
The priest replied to her: 'Why?'.

00:55:25.572 --> 00:55:28.158
One lady from the 
group started shouting:

00:55:28.158 --> 00:55:30.702
'If she wants a Bible, she obviously
is seeking guidance and an 

00:55:30.702 --> 00:55:32.829
answer through the Bible!'.

00:55:33.413 --> 00:55:35.582
The priest turned around
and asked: 'Is that true?'

00:55:35.790 --> 00:55:37.334
Katarina answered that it was true.

00:55:37.584 --> 00:55:38.251
New Caption

00:55:38.668 --> 00:55:41.629
She knelt, he lifted his
arms, prayed over her,

00:55:42.255 --> 00:55:44.841
blessed her and 
gave her the Bible.

00:55:45.383 --> 00:55:48.178
At the mountain top Cross, Katarina said:

00:55:48.178 --> 00:55:50.847
'My Jesus. What should I do?

00:55:50.847 --> 00:55:52.223
Goran wants to marry me,

00:55:52.223 --> 00:55:55.352
but I'm afraid. What if he 
starts to take drugs again?

00:55:55.977 --> 00:55:57.562
What if he starts to drink?

00:55:57.562 --> 00:55:59.230
What if he starts beating me?

00:55:59.230 --> 00:56:01.149
I have to have him 
for the rest of my life.

00:56:01.483 --> 00:56:02.192
Jesus

00:56:02.192 --> 00:56:05.445
I don't know if marriage is my
path, is this my calling in life.

00:56:05.987 --> 00:56:08.698
Goran wants us to live in 
Medjugorje our whole lives,

00:56:08.698 --> 00:56:10.658
I don't know anybody here.
What will I do here?'.

00:56:11.034 --> 00:56:12.786
These were all reasonable questions.

00:56:12.786 --> 00:56:14.996
She prayed and prayed and prayed.

00:56:15.330 --> 00:56:17.207
Finally with her eyes closed,

00:56:18.249 --> 00:56:19.542
she opened the Bible

00:56:19.542 --> 00:56:21.002
and where her eyes landed,

00:56:21.002 --> 00:56:22.003
that's what she read

00:56:22.754 --> 00:56:24.005
and it said:

00:56:25.090 --> 00:56:26.758
Stay where you are,

00:56:26.758 --> 00:56:28.259
that is your path.

00:56:28.259 --> 00:56:29.260
don't be afraid,

00:56:29.260 --> 00:56:30.387
I am with you.

00:56:30.720 --> 00:56:33.681
So, it was nicely written...

00:56:33.681 --> 00:56:36.643
marry Goran.

00:56:38.812 --> 00:56:40.063
Very simple.

00:56:44.859 --> 00:56:46.778
I see that you're laughing.

00:56:46.778 --> 00:56:48.071
Simple, isn't it?

00:56:53.701 --> 00:56:55.703
But again, there were problems

00:56:55.703 --> 00:56:57.247
and why?

00:56:57.664 --> 00:56:58.832
I'll tell you why

00:56:59.791 --> 00:57:03.420
there were problems, because
Katarina is a woman. 

00:57:04.379 --> 00:57:09.509
Sorry ladies, but you always
complicate simple things.

00:57:10.218 --> 00:57:12.512
Man, it was clearly written 
right there, in black and white,

00:57:13.179 --> 00:57:14.722
but she was still unsure.

00:57:15.807 --> 00:57:18.268
She closed the Bible,
returned it to the priest

00:57:18.268 --> 00:57:19.894
and started to make
her way back down.

00:57:20.895 --> 00:57:22.730
She made ten or so steps

00:57:24.107 --> 00:57:25.525
and she stopped

00:57:25.859 --> 00:57:26.943
turned

00:57:27.318 --> 00:57:29.112
and looked at the priest.

00:57:29.696 --> 00:57:30.697
At that moment

00:57:32.323 --> 00:57:33.575
she had remembered something.

00:57:36.286 --> 00:57:39.330
When Katarina was 
eleven and a half years old.

00:57:39.706 --> 00:57:42.876
From the north of the Czech Republic,
she went to the south

00:57:42.876 --> 00:57:45.044
on vacation, to her grandmother's.

00:57:45.044 --> 00:57:47.714
One morning, she went to holy 
mass with her old grandmother,

00:57:47.714 --> 00:57:49.591
which was celebrated
by a young priest.

00:57:49.591 --> 00:57:50.967
The mass ended.

00:57:50.967 --> 00:57:54.220
The priest came down from 
the alter and came to her and said:

00:57:54.929 --> 00:57:56.139
'Little girl,

00:57:56.139 --> 00:57:57.515
please kneel.

00:57:57.515 --> 00:57:59.851
I will pray for your calling in life,

00:57:59.851 --> 00:58:01.394
and for your life's path

00:58:01.394 --> 00:58:03.980
and I will always be praying
for you from now on.'

00:58:04.731 --> 00:58:08.443
Katarina kneeled, he raised 
his arms and prayed over her.

00:58:09.611 --> 00:58:10.820
From that moment on,

00:58:11.446 --> 00:58:12.822
for the next twelve years,

00:58:12.822 --> 00:58:16.284
she never saw that priest again.

00:58:16.618 --> 00:58:20.371
That priest, was the same priest 
on Križevac Hill, which lent her his Bible.

00:58:20.371 --> 00:58:21.498
That was him.

00:58:21.498 --> 00:58:26.294
It was in this moment, that she 
was certain that it was God's will.

00:58:26.628 --> 00:58:28.963
We have been in contact with that
priest for a long time ever since.

00:58:28.963 --> 00:58:30.423
He comes here often

00:58:30.840 --> 00:58:35.053
He comes here often with his 
pilgrims, to hear my testimony.

00:58:35.136 --> 00:58:36.638
What's also interesting,

00:58:37.055 --> 00:58:38.848
is that the church in the south

00:58:38.848 --> 00:58:41.059
where that priest prayed over her,

00:58:41.267 --> 00:58:42.810
was the church of St. Jacob

00:58:43.770 --> 00:58:45.480
June 3, 2000

00:58:45.813 --> 00:58:48.983
Katarina and I got married
in St. Jacob's church,

00:58:48.983 --> 00:58:50.318
but not the one in the Czech Republic,

00:58:50.318 --> 00:58:51.653
rather the one here in Medjugorje.

00:58:51.653 --> 00:58:53.738
We now have Lucija, eighteen years old,

00:58:53.738 --> 00:58:55.031
Luka, fifteen,

00:58:55.031 --> 00:58:56.491
Ana, thirteen,

00:58:56.491 --> 00:58:57.617
Marko, nine

00:58:57.617 --> 00:58:59.285
and little Jan is five years old.

00:58:59.577 --> 00:59:00.870
We have five children.

00:59:18.638 --> 00:59:21.224
Praise be and glory to God.
Nobody else.

00:59:22.267 --> 00:59:23.518
As for my stepmother,

00:59:25.353 --> 00:59:27.063
whom I wanted to kill twice,

00:59:27.063 --> 00:59:28.273
how much I hated her,

00:59:29.482 --> 00:59:33.611
paid a holy mass every month for
my salvation and conversion

00:59:33.611 --> 00:59:37.782
during the nine years 
I was living on the streets.

00:59:38.032 --> 00:59:40.952
She never got tired. 
She never lost hope.

00:59:40.952 --> 00:59:43.079
She never stopped believing in me.

00:59:43.329 --> 00:59:44.998
She wasn't even my mother.

00:59:44.998 --> 00:59:47.792
All that love which I didn't give 
my biological mother, 

00:59:47.792 --> 00:59:49.043
because I was stupid,

00:59:49.043 --> 00:59:50.837
I now give to her.

00:59:50.837 --> 00:59:52.005
My father is still alive

00:59:52.005 --> 00:59:53.673
he's eighty-six years old.

00:59:53.673 --> 00:59:57.427
I think he'll live longer than me.
The old guy is doing great.

00:59:58.803 --> 01:00:01.681
My brother hasn't drank alcohol
for many years.

01:00:01.681 --> 01:00:04.809
His wife is also deaf and mute.
They have two healthy daughters.

01:00:05.602 --> 01:00:07.770
From the day I came to Medjugorje

01:00:07.770 --> 01:00:09.897
I have never had an epileptic attack.

01:00:09.897 --> 01:00:12.775
All the paranoia and fear I had 
in this crazy head, have disappeared.

01:00:12.775 --> 01:00:14.652
Now, I only fear God and my wife.

01:00:15.695 --> 01:00:18.072
My Czech woman is as 
dangerous as a wildfire,

01:00:18.698 --> 01:00:20.658
but that's good for me.

01:00:21.951 --> 01:00:24.662
Due to the bullet in my head, they 
didn't even give me one year to live,

01:00:24.662 --> 01:00:25.872
not one more year

01:00:26.289 --> 01:00:27.582
On June 2nd

01:00:27.874 --> 01:00:33.379
of last year, it was full forty-one years
since I shot that bullet into my head.

01:00:34.047 --> 01:00:38.468
The other day my son Luka, 
thought about it and said to me:

01:00:39.093 --> 01:00:41.012
'You know Dad, you're
a really lucky guy.'

01:00:41.512 --> 01:00:44.098
' I asked him: 'Why am I lucky?'

01:00:44.098 --> 01:00:45.600
and he said: 'Look,

01:00:45.600 --> 01:00:48.061
nobody can ever tell you 
you have nothing in your head.'

01:00:57.820 --> 01:00:59.947
If you wish to ask questions,

01:01:00.406 --> 01:01:01.908
you can.

01:01:04.118 --> 01:01:05.411
Any questions?

01:01:22.845 --> 01:01:25.098
&lt;i&gt;What do you do?&lt;/i&gt;

01:01:26.099 --> 01:01:28.685
When I entered the rehab community,

01:01:34.148 --> 01:01:36.192
Sister Elvira heard my story

01:01:37.485 --> 01:01:39.028
and told the other guys:

01:01:41.030 --> 01:01:43.908
'Place this new guy in 
our icon painting classes

01:01:43.908 --> 01:01:45.993
when his withdrawal period is over.'

01:01:48.663 --> 01:01:51.624
So, today I am in essence,
an iconographer.

01:01:52.709 --> 01:01:54.627
I've promised an icon to my
best man three years ago,

01:01:54.627 --> 01:01:57.296
he's going to kill me because 
I still haven't delivered him one,

01:01:57.839 --> 01:02:00.800
it doesn't matter, it's all
good, you'll get it.

01:02:01.467 --> 01:02:05.138
Like I said, she placed me
in iconography classes,

01:02:07.348 --> 01:02:08.558
because when you
draw icons of God,

01:02:09.058 --> 01:02:10.268
you have to be pure,

01:02:10.518 --> 01:02:12.729
you have to pray and fast.

01:02:13.187 --> 01:02:15.106
That was surely

01:02:15.106 --> 01:02:18.067
one of the ways

01:02:18.776 --> 01:02:21.404
that helped me in my spiritual

01:02:21.863 --> 01:02:23.698
conversion and healing.

01:02:24.240 --> 01:02:26.242
So, I am an iconographer.

01:02:26.242 --> 01:02:29.203
However, there's a little problem,

01:02:31.831 --> 01:02:36.377
from March to November, I have
three, four testimonies per day.

01:02:37.295 --> 01:02:39.630
So I don't have 
much time to work on

01:02:40.423 --> 01:02:41.674
work on icons

01:02:41.966 --> 01:02:43.634
My wife is a guide

01:02:47.597 --> 01:02:49.599
for Czech and Slovak pilgirm groups.

01:02:49.599 --> 01:02:52.018
So when she is with her pilgrim
groups, I take care of our kids. 

01:02:52.018 --> 01:02:54.312
What am I to do, we have five 
children. I have to study with them.

01:02:54.312 --> 01:02:57.648
When she's home, then I do 
my testimonies and that's how

01:02:57.648 --> 01:02:59.066
we survive from day to day.

01:02:59.442 --> 01:03:00.943
Those are in essence,

01:03:00.943 --> 01:03:01.944
our jobs.

01:03:10.787 --> 01:03:14.749
After sweeping washrooms, I also 
worked at sweeping the parish office,

01:03:15.458 --> 01:03:17.752
here I was in charge of registering Mass
offerings from parishioners, who would

01:03:17.752 --> 01:03:19.212
pay Masses for their deceased.

01:03:19.212 --> 01:03:22.507
There were funny stories there as well, 
but I won't burden you with them tonight.

01:03:22.840 --> 01:03:24.842
But, people would come from Split
to pay a Mass for their deceased, 

01:03:24.842 --> 01:03:26.719
and when they saw me sitting there in
the office they would immediately run

01:03:26.719 --> 01:03:27.678
away from the office.

01:03:31.307 --> 01:03:33.643
Then they would go back to Split 
and tell everyone that they saw me,

01:03:33.643 --> 01:03:36.187
and that I even succeeded in 
conning the friars in Medjugorje.

01:03:38.356 --> 01:03:41.317
During a Mass once, I was doing 
the Mass collection,

01:03:41.317 --> 01:03:44.946
and one guy grabbed me by
the neck and said that I had

01:03:44.946 --> 01:03:47.448
cheated him for 
money back in Spilt.

01:03:51.202 --> 01:03:52.662
Sorry, I've gotten off topic

01:03:53.621 --> 01:03:58.793
After the parish office, the friars
suggested that I go work in

01:03:58.793 --> 01:04:01.754
government office in The Center
for the fight against drugs,

01:04:02.088 --> 01:04:03.798
which had just opened in Mostar.

01:04:03.798 --> 01:04:07.176
There I did seminars with
the police, doctors, etc.

01:04:07.176 --> 01:04:09.554
They took me in and I 
worked there for a long time.

01:04:09.554 --> 01:04:12.765
I went around Mostar and picked
up drug addicts off the streets.

01:04:12.765 --> 01:04:17.019
I would take their heroin, weed, 
everything they had, pills, everything.

01:04:19.647 --> 01:04:22.817
Then I would flush it all down the toilet.

01:04:26.904 --> 01:04:29.740
Once they called me on a Friday night,

01:04:29.740 --> 01:04:32.702
Saturday and Sundays we didn't work,

01:04:33.202 --> 01:04:35.580
from Caritas and told me 
that they received from Italy

01:04:35.580 --> 01:04:38.541
two bags of Heptanone and Methadone.

01:04:39.041 --> 01:04:40.543
That's a replacement for heroin.

01:04:41.252 --> 01:04:45.548
So I went to Mostar, and I kept the
methadone for two days

01:04:46.340 --> 01:04:47.258
in my house

01:04:47.258 --> 01:04:50.219
and it didn't even cross my mind

01:04:51.345 --> 01:04:56.225
to take the drugs. That was more of a
grace, than it was my strength.

01:04:57.184 --> 01:04:58.853
It never crossed my mind.

01:04:58.853 --> 01:05:02.481
The only time it's hard not to drink
is when football (soccer) matches are played,

01:05:02.481 --> 01:05:04.483
when Champions league or Croatian 
National team matches are played on TV,

01:05:04.483 --> 01:05:05.985
we are all watching in a cafe,

01:05:05.985 --> 01:05:09.113
then I feel like drinking a beer. Everyone
is drinking beer, and I drink juice.

01:05:09.113 --> 01:05:11.365
I can't even look at it anymore.

01:05:11.365 --> 01:05:14.452
Then I order a coffee, then another 
coffee, then I get an upset stomach.

01:05:14.744 --> 01:05:17.705
That's the only time
I feel like drinking a beer,

01:05:17.830 --> 01:05:21.083
but I said I wouldn’t
drink and I haven't.

01:05:21.542 --> 01:05:23.628
I still haven't given in and I won't.

01:05:23.628 --> 01:05:25.046
Now I'm already old.

01:05:34.013 --> 01:05:36.974
A battle is a battle, with 
everything and anything,

01:05:36.974 --> 01:05:39.185
but the hardest battle is with yourself.

01:05:39.185 --> 01:05:42.104
Then with your wife, your
children, your neighbors.

01:05:42.104 --> 01:05:44.398
Every day is a battle, 
every day is a conversion.

01:05:44.398 --> 01:05:47.360
Every day I ask God
for the mercy to be

01:05:47.860 --> 01:05:49.362
a better man.

01:05:51.322 --> 01:05:53.783
At home, we try not only to pray

01:05:56.994 --> 01:05:57.912
the rosary,

01:05:57.912 --> 01:05:59.872
but to also put our prayers into deeds.

01:05:59.872 --> 01:06:04.168
This means being good towards
other people, helping others.

01:06:04.168 --> 01:06:06.587
Please don't take me wrong, 
that I'm praising myself or something,

01:06:06.587 --> 01:06:08.422
but it's from God, not from me.

01:06:08.422 --> 01:06:13.678
My wife and I placed over sixty guys
and girls in the rehab center,

01:06:14.595 --> 01:06:16.764
through dialogue.

01:06:17.223 --> 01:06:21.644
Then when somebody comes to you 
from Poland, Ireland, or from wherever,

01:06:21.644 --> 01:06:23.980
and they thank you for saving them,

01:06:26.983 --> 01:06:29.360
that is the joy that gives you life.

01:06:30.778 --> 01:06:34.365
I have had it up until here,
with these witnessing.

01:06:34.365 --> 01:06:36.951
I have no desire to 
speak about it anymore.

01:06:36.951 --> 01:06:39.620
Every day I witness three, four times.

01:06:40.496 --> 01:06:41.622
Last year

01:06:41.622 --> 01:06:45.292
I wasn't eating, drinking, I just
sat in front of the house and

01:06:45.292 --> 01:06:47.336
kept repeating the same thing.

01:06:51.966 --> 01:06:54.593
I really fell into some kind of crisis.

01:06:55.177 --> 01:06:57.471
I kneeled in the kitchen and said:

01:06:57.471 --> 01:07:01.726
'My Jesus, please let me know

01:07:02.268 --> 01:07:05.730
whether these witnessing
are my mission or not.

01:07:06.022 --> 01:07:10.901
Please, if they are not little by
little, let the people leave,

01:07:11.527 --> 01:07:13.070
and if it is my mission,

01:07:14.321 --> 01:07:15.740
send more.

01:07:16.449 --> 01:07:18.868
That was the biggest mistake I made

01:07:22.079 --> 01:07:24.498
It was the biggest mistake I ever made

01:07:25.833 --> 01:07:28.794
If I had the strength

01:07:28.794 --> 01:07:31.464
well, I would have 
ten testimonies a day.

01:07:31.464 --> 01:07:32.631
I'm so stupid,

01:07:32.631 --> 01:07:36.594
If I didn't ask Jesus, I could have been
happy with one, two testimonies daily.

01:07:36.886 --> 01:07:38.137
Now man,

01:07:39.638 --> 01:07:42.099
it is completely out of control

01:07:45.811 --> 01:07:48.522
To be honest, I still haven't accepted
that this is my life's mission.

01:07:48.522 --> 01:07:51.400
I haven't accepted it, but 
wherever they call me to go,

01:07:51.400 --> 01:07:52.526
I go

01:07:54.779 --> 01:07:57.823
I go, because when parents call 
me or come to my door and say:

01:07:57.823 --> 01:07:59.909
'My child has been going to the 
rehab commune for three years.'

01:07:59.909 --> 01:08:02.703
or 'My child got out and got married.
Thank you very much.'

01:08:02.703 --> 01:08:04.163
That in essence gives me....

01:08:04.163 --> 01:08:07.124
I see the fruits and that gives me

01:08:07.958 --> 01:08:10.544
the strength to go forward.

01:08:16.217 --> 01:08:20.179
Where has God lead you? 
Where have you witnessed?

01:08:21.388 --> 01:08:26.769
Well, I was in Dublin with Vicka.
There were about ten priests.

01:08:29.897 --> 01:08:32.733
That was where I spoke in
front of the most people. 

01:08:35.611 --> 01:08:37.071
There were 5500 people.

01:08:38.364 --> 01:08:41.325
I was in Dublin in 2004.

01:08:41.867 --> 01:08:46.413
I went to the Ukraine four times.
I was in England, in Ireland 

01:08:47.665 --> 01:08:50.626
in Italy. Now I will be
going to Slovakia,

01:08:51.043 --> 01:08:53.045
but my favorite is going to prisons.

01:08:54.255 --> 01:08:57.424
You guys here tonight don't have prison 
problems, for you it's nice to listen to me.

01:09:02.138 --> 01:09:04.640
But when I go to prisons, to
their psychiatric wards,

01:09:04.890 --> 01:09:06.642
I feel at home there.

01:09:19.196 --> 01:09:21.198
I need prisoners,

01:09:22.741 --> 01:09:24.952
I need those in psychiatry

01:09:24.952 --> 01:09:27.830
and that's what I like most.
When I go there, I know that

01:09:27.830 --> 01:09:30.791
there I can make a difference,
My testimony can bear fruit there.

01:09:34.837 --> 01:09:37.298
Thank you, thank you from the heart. 
I kindly ask for no one to take offence

01:09:37.298 --> 01:09:38.591
if I offended them in any way.

